{"type":"message","id":"a0e4a9fe","parentId":"571c1ba6","timestamp":"2026-05-08T06:21:32.330Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ft2nf4ytg645_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/e22921cf-659e-4149-bdea-afcfc1b48d8f.trajectory.jsonl:{\"traceSchema\":\"openclaw-trajectory\",\"schemaVersion\":1,\"traceId\":\"e22921cf-659e-4149-bdea-afcfc1b48d8f\",\"source\":\"runtime\",\"type\":\"context.compiled\",\"ts\":\"2026-05-08T06:19:57.732Z\",\"seq\":3,\"sourceSeq\":3,\"sessionId\":\"e22921cf-659e-4149-bdea-afcfc1b48d8f\",\"sessionKey\":\"agent:main:telegram:direct:robberzaz\",\"runId\":\"343a5bda-11b4-41fc-8657-11e6bf57ca31\",\"workspaceDir\":\"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace\",\"provider\":\"minimax\",\"modelId\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"modelApi\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"data\":{\"systemPrompt\":{\"truncated\":true,\"reason\":\"trajectory-field-size-limit\",\"originalChars\":47934,\"limitChars\":32768},\"prompt\":\"\\\"มึงไปอ่าน ~/.openclaw/config.yaml ตรงส่วน systemInstruction มาเทียบกับกฎใน ~/.hermes/memories/MEMORY.md และ USER.md ดูซิว่ามันขัดแย้งกันตรงไหนไหม? โดยเฉพาะเรื่องการรายงานสถานะ (Emoji), การลบ Log, และการโยนงานให้ Hermes... ถ้าไม่ตรงกัน ให้สรุปจุดที่ต้องแก้มาให้กู!\\\"\",\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"หาทาง ปิดไฟใน cpu led หลายๆสี\"}],\"timestamp\":1778199757505},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"เจ้านายถามเรื่องปิดไฟ CPU LED หลายสี ซึ่งน่าจะหมายถึงพีซีของเขา (Windows/Wsl) ที่มีไฟ LED หลายสีบน CPU หรืออุปกรณ์คอม\\n\\nให้ช่วยหาวิธีปิดไฟ LED หลายสีบน CPU - นี่อาจเป็นเรื่องของ:\\n1. CPU cooler RGB\\n2. Motherboard RGB\\n3. Case fans RGB\\n4. หรืออุปกรณ์อื่นๆ\\n\\nต้องถามเจ้านายก่อนว่าอุปกรณ์ของเขาเป็นยี่ห้ออะไร เพราะแต่ละยี่ห้อใช้ซอฟต์แวร์ต่างกัน:\\n- Corsair: iCUE\\n- NZXT: CAM\\n- ASUS: Armoury Crate / ASUS Aura\\n- MSI: MSI Center\\n- Gigabyte: RGB Fusion\\n- Razer: Razer Synapse\\n\\nแต่ก่อนจะถาม ให้ลองหาข้อมูลใน memory ดูก่อนว่าเคยมีข้อมูลเกี่ยวกับคอมของเจ้านายหรือเปล่า\\n\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"8efd6d90c4dd60dec47c560c16b54f2eb5e5e20c6df841c1892d923915479fd0\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\n🧑🏼💻 ขอถามอุปกรณ์ที่มีไฟ LED RGB ของเจ้านายหน่อยครับ เพราะแต่ละยี่ห้อใช้ซอฟต์แวร์ต่างกันเลย\\n\\n**รุ่นอะไรครับ?**\\n\\n- 🔹 **CPU Cooler** — Corsair, Cooler Master, NZXT, DeepCool?\\n- 🔹 **เมนบอร์ด** — ASUS, MSI, Gigabyte, ASRock?\\n- 🔹 **Case Fan** — มีหลายตัวไหม?\\n- 🔹 **อื่นๆ** — เช่น RAM, GPU, หรือ case ที่มี built-in RGB?\\n\\nพอรู้ยี่ห้อและรุ่นแล้วจะได้แนะนำวิธีปิดไฟถูกครับ 🧑🏼💻\"}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"minimax\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"usage\":{\"input\":32893,\"output\":681,\"cacheRead\":64,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":33638,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1778199757508,\"responseId\":\"064c5fd1850d1280d96f34f21c0cb848\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ไม่รู้ ทางทาง ดูข้อมูลเอง\"}],\"timestamp\":1778199796826},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"เจ้านายบอกให้หาข้อมูลเอง ไม่รู้ว่าอุปกรณ์รุ่นอะไร ผมจะค้นหาวิธีปิด CPU LED RGB แบบทั่วไปก่อน แล้วแบ่งตามยี่ห้อต่างๆ ให้\\n\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"7da5855ccc9673cb746680415ea8dcf73619b27a09b2a787ddc99be6b0297e1d\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_vihza3arp45n_1\",\"name\":\"web_search\",\"arguments\":{\"query\":\"how to turn off CPU LED RGB light multi color software control\"}}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"minimax\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"usage\":{\"input\":33003,\"output\":149,\"cacheRead\":256,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":33408,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1778199796829,\"responseId\":\"064c5ff87c7e665196a5bdf58d88f50a\"},{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_function_vihza3arp45n_1\",\"toolName\":\"web_search\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"query\\\": \\\"how to turn off CPU LED RGB light multi color software control\\\",\\n  \\\"provider\\\": \\\"duckduckgo\\\",\\n  \\\"count\\\": 5,\\n  \\\"tookMs\\\": 1126,\\n  \\\"externalContent\\\": {\\n    \\\"untrusted\\\": true,\\n    \\\"source\\\": \\\"web_search\\\",\\n    \\\"provider\\\": \\\"duckduckgo\\\",\\n    \\\"wrapped\\\": true\\n  },\\n  \\\"results\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"a23fb3439eba9e3b\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nHow to Disable RGB (LED) Lighting on Your Computer\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"a23fb3439eba9e3b\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.majorgeeks.com/content/page/disable_rgb.html\\\",\\n      \\\"snippet\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"80f354ec06a3d51b\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nGigabyte RGB Fusion Cooler Master Thermaltake How to Disable RGB Lighting on Your Computer - Motherboard Some computers, for example, the Hewlett Packard Envy and Omen series, have RGB lighting for the logo and the inside of the tower. Unlike most RGB lighting, you can often disable this light by removing the power from the pins on the motherboard.\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"80f354ec06a3d51b\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"siteName\\\": \\\"www.majorgeeks.com\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"73b478ec4d50a430\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nHow to turn off RGB on a Windows 11/10 PC - The Windows Club\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"73b478ec4d50a430\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.thewindowsclub.com/how-to-turn-off-rgb-on-a-windows-11-10-pc\\\",\\n      \\\"snippet\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"c232e827385d4c84\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nIs RGB causing too much light on your PC? To turn off RGB or customize it to be less distracting, configure the BIOS or use OpenRGB Software .\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"c232e827385d4c84\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"siteName\\\": \\\"www.thewindowsclub.com\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"38e2fba64748ad44\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nHow to Turn Off RGB Lights on PC Windows 11: Total Control Guide\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"38e2fba64748ad44\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://techradar.info/how-to-turn-off-rgb-lights-on-pc-windows-11-total-control-guide/\\\",\\n      \\\"snippet\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"700f84c3b1eae19f\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nImpact of Disabling RGB on System Performance Beyond aesthetics, turning off RGB lights on PC Windows 11 can have minor technical benefits. LED controllers and the software required to run them consume CPU cycles and system memory. In extreme cases, poorly optimized RGB software can cause \\\\\\\"micro-stuttering\\\\\\\" in high-performance gaming scenarios.\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"700f84c3b1eae19f\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"siteName\\\": \\\"techradar.info\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"86000c92de4ae677\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nOpenRGB\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"86000c92de4ae677\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://openrgb.org/\\\",\\n      \\\"snippet\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"177d5af6b7ce6290\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nControl RGB without wasting system resources Lightweight User Interface OpenRGB keeps it simple with a lightweight user interface that doesn't waste background resources with excessive custom images and styles. It is light on both RAM and CPU usage, so your system can continue to shine without cutting into your gaming or productivity performance.\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"177d5af6b7ce6290\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"siteName\\\": \\\"openrgb.org\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"a61ee3a7b2d282c4\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nPC RGB Too Bright at Night? Turn Off LED Lights Fast\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"a61ee3a7b2d282c4\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.coohom.com/article/how-to-turn-off-led-lights-on-your-pc\\\",\\n      \\\"snippet\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"c81e093da14c68cf\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nLearn how to turn off PC LED lights using motherboard apps, BIOS settings, fan controllers, and peripheral software .\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"c81e093da14c68cf\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"siteName\\\": \\\"www.coohom.com\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\"}],\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1778199809266},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Let me search for more specific info about BIOS settings and software options.\\n\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"efd037a50b261ebeebd578dfbb4745af262d413aaddb205e50a9c4963661a010\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_onofouw3bjwt_1\",\"name\":\"web_search\",\"arguments\":{\"query\":\"how to disable RGB LED BIOS settings motherboard without software\"}}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"minimax\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"usage\":{\"input\":1299,\"output\":49,\"cacheRead\":33216,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":34564,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1778199809268,\"responseId\":\"064c600210b2a9e34f1e9c3c10ad34a4\"},{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_function_onofouw3bjwt_1\",\"toolName\":\"web_search\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"query\\\": \\\"how to disable RGB LED BIOS settings motherboard without software\\\",\\n  \\\"provider\\\": \\\"duckduckgo\\\",\\n  \\\"count\\\": 5,\\n  \\\"tookMs\\\": 863,\\n  \\\"externalContent\\\": {\\n    \\\"untrusted\\\": true,\\n    \\\"source\\\": \\\"web_search\\\",\\n    \\\"provider\\\": \\\"duckduckgo\\\",\\n    \\\"wrapped\\\": true\\n  },\\n  \\\"results\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"1a290a0b88c077ff\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nCan I turn off all the LED lights on the motherboard in BIOS?\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"1a290a0b88c077ff\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.msi.com/faq/3532\\\",\\n      \\\"snippet\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"d22b0ecdfbce38f4\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nAnswer You could enter BIOS setup and disable RGB Light Control and Indication LED Control, press F10 to Save & Exit, by doing this you could turn off all the LEDs on the motherboard except for EZ Debug LEDs .\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"d22b0ecdfbce38f4\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"siteName\\\": \\\"www.msi.com\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"0ca3eb443b0ace22\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nThe Ultimate Guide to Disabling RGB Lights on PC Fans Without Extra ...\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"0ca3eb443b0ace22\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://smart.dhgate.com/the-ultimate-guide-to-disabling-rgb-lights-on-pc-fans-without-extra-software/\\\",\\n      \\\"snippet\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"b1f9b36130b8a75c\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nUse your motherboard BIOS settings : Believe it or not, some BIOS interfaces let you disable RGB lighting without Windows software . Dive into your BIOS menu, search for onboard LED or lighting settings , and toggle those off.\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"b1f9b36130b8a75c\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"siteName\\\": \\\"smart.dhgate.com\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"be381964c320cc67\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nHow to Disable RGB (LED) Lighting on Your Computer\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"be381964c320cc67\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.majorgeeks.com/content/page/disable_rgb.html\\\",\\n      \\\"snippet\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"ea9b208e54388546\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nYou should be able to locate your motherboard manual online to find what pins power your RGB lighting. How to Disable RGB Lighting on Your Computer - BIOS The BIOS , much like the motherboard , is best used if you have some experience. This is because every BIOS is different, so the settings for RGB will be different for every brand motherboard .\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"ea9b208e54388546\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"siteName\\\": \\\"www.majorgeeks.com\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"5ae3469038ea3599\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nHow to turn off RGB on a Windows 11/10 PC - The Windows Club\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTE\n\n⚠️ [... middle content omitted — showing head and tail ...]\n\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/e22921cf-659e-4149-bdea-afcfc1b48d8f.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"38b79eaf\",\"parentId\":\"aabf9dcc\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-08T06:21:11.026Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Let me also check the identity file for systemInstruction.\\n\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"3224bb3d68347dee9cb066bc25ffc85a3bac1ac4539c58a7a97578af89da3044\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_3aifplivklcq_1\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"cat ~/.openclaw/identity/device.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json,sys\\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\\nprint(json.dumps(d, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)[:3000])\\n\\\"\",\"timeout\":5}},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_3aifplivklcq_2\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json,sys\\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\\n# Check gateway config\\ngw = d.get('gateway', {})\\nfor k,v in gw.items():\\n    if isinstance(v, str):\\n        print(f'gateway.{k}: {v[:200]}')\\n    elif isinstance(v, dict):\\n        print(f'gateway.{k}: {list(v.keys())}')\\n    elif isinstance(v, list):\\n        print(f'gateway.{k}: list[{len(v)}]')\\n    else:\\n        print(f'gateway.{k}: {type(v).__name__}')\\n\\\" 2>/dev/null\",\"timeout\":5}}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"minimax\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"usage\":{\"input\":378,\"output\":257,\"cacheRead\":51200,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":51835,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1778221264018,\"responseId\":\"064cb3d17aa3f3805ee4d848e590d447\"}}\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/e22921cf-659e-4149-bdea-afcfc1b48d8f.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"4f3a039f\",\"parentId\":\"20e811d2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-08T06:21:27.357Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"I don't see a systemInstruction in the openclaw.json config at all. Let me check if OpenClaw has a different way to set system instructions - maybe through the agents config or through the identity files.\\n\\nLet me look for a systemInstruction in the entire OpenClaw config structure or check if there's a separate config file.\\n\\nActually, looking at the question again - the user asked me to look at `~/.openclaw/config.yaml` specifically. But that file doesn't exist. Maybe it's `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` that acts as the config, and there might be a systemInstruction somewhere in it.\\n\\nWait - looking at my startup context, there are injected \\\"Project Context\\\" files. \\n\\nThe systemInstruction might be injected at runtime by OpenClaw rather than stored as a file. Looking at the files I have access to - SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md - none of these contain the specific \\\"systemInstruction\\\" field the user mentioned. Let me check if there's a systemInstruction in OpenClaw's agent configuration or identity settings that I might have missed.\\n\\nThe user mentioned comparing three sources but config.yaml doesn't seem to exist, so I should check OpenClaw's documentation to understand how system instructions are actually configured in this system.\\n\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"6fb3ab2143920ed6cdb50f7611f123395dba1acf41fc66b986f5bd624a785df8\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_ft2nf4ytg645_1\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"ls ~/.openclaw/agents/ 2>/dev/null && cat ~/.openclaw/agents/*.yaml 2>/dev/null || cat ~/.openclaw/agents/*.json 2>/dev/null | head -200\",\"timeout\":5}},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_ft2nf4ytg645_2\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"grep -r \\\"systemInstruction\\\" ~/.openclaw/ 2>/dev/null | head -20\",\"timeout\":5}}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"minimax\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"usage\":{\"input\":558,\"output\":384,\"cacheRead\":51520,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":52462,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1778221271075,\"responseId\":\"064cb3d92df62f9ed3ec53f5feb2b344\"}}[... 88525 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace","exitCode"