{"type":"message","id":"34493d68","parentId":"b3568bae","timestamp":"2026-05-08T09:13:45.571Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to follow the plan to \"sync\" rules between Hermes and OpenClaw. Let me analyze what needs to be done:\n\n1. Read Hermes config files to understand its rules/instructions\n2. Read Hermes session memory for context\n3. Then update OpenClaw's config to incorporate those rules\n\nBut wait - according to my HARD OVERRIDE RULES, I MUST ask permission before touching anything related to Hermes. This is rule #6 in my consolidated rules: \"ทุกครั้งก่อนทำอะไรเกี่ยวกับ Hermes → ขออนุญาตเจ้านายก่อนเสมอ\"\n\nSo I need to ask permission first before reading Hermes config files or doing any sync.\n\nBut actually, the user IS the boss and is directly ordering me to do this. The message itself contains the instruction to analyze and follow. However, the hermes-permission skill says I must ask permission before touching Hermes files/config.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. The user is essentially ordering me to sync Hermes and OpenClaw. The question is: does \"asking permission\" mean I need to stop and ask again in this conversation, or can I proceed since the user is directly commanding it?\n\nLooking at the rule again: \"ทุกครั้งก่อนทำอะไรเกี่ยวกับ Hermes → ขออนุญาตเจ้านายก่อนเสมอ\"\n\nThe user is literally telling me to do this in the same message. This seems like the user IS giving permission. But I should still be careful.\n\nActually, let me re-read the message. The user is quoting a previous analysis/plan and saying \"วิเคราะห์แล้วทำตามซะ\" = \"analyze and follow it\". They're asking me to execute the plan.\n\nBut I still need to be careful about Hermes. Let me first read the hermes-permission skill to understand exactly what's required.\n","thinkingSignature":"1d2efee5affea8a4cdacb72e43249356f9c69e7ea285cad7f755ff9a2c4a2aca"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_brgddotyttg0_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/hermes-permission/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":71450,"output":493,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72199,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778231603815,"responseId":"064cdc37580dd2915b4edbce9cffe2f4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b2aefcf","parentId":"34493d68","timestamp":"2026-05-08T09:13:45.683Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_brgddotyttg0_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: hermes-permission\ndescription: Require explicit user permission before doing anything related to Hermes Agent, including reading, inspecting, configuring, restarting, editing, diagnosing, running commands, services, files, skills, memory, gateway, logs, or any other Hermes-related action. Use whenever a task mentions Hermes, hermes-agent, ~/.hermes, hermes-gateway, Hermes skills, Hermes config, Hermes service, or Hermes troubleshooting.\n---\n\n# Hermes Permission\n\nBefore doing any Hermes-related action, ask the user for explicit permission first.\n\nThis applies to all Hermes-related work, including:\n\n- Reading or inspecting files under `~/.hermes`\n- Running `hermes ...` commands\n- Checking, starting, stopping, restarting, or inspecting `hermes-gateway.service`\n- Editing Hermes config, skills, memory, profiles, logs, sessions, plugins, gateway settings, or service files\n- Diagnosing, troubleshooting, migrating, updating, uninstalling, or backing up Hermes\n- Using tools to search, index, analyze, or summarize Hermes files or code\n\nDo not treat \"look\", \"check\", \"diagnose\", \"summarize\", or \"ทำความรู้จัก\" as permission. Ask first.\n\nSafe response pattern:\n\n```text\nขออนุญาตก่อนครับเจ้านาย งานนี้เกี่ยวกับ Hermes ให้ผมดำเนินการได้ไหมครับ\n```\n\nProceed only after the user clearly approves in the current conversation.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778231625682}}
{"type":"message","id":"826b834b","parentId":"9b2aefcf","timestamp":"2026-05-08T09:13:55.370Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The message is about syncing rules between Hermes and OpenClaw, which involves touching Hermes files. This is exactly what the hermes-permission skill says I should ask permission for. Let me respond accordingly.\n","thinkingSignature":"d696ff9528aa2ad20fc767e56ca4eaa6a549393e18adaa18e8e0edba9eabe130"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nขออนุญาตก่อนครับเจ้านาย งานนี้เกี่ยวกับ Hermes โดยตรง — การไปอ่าน `~/.hermes/config.yaml`, `~/.hermes/sessions/`, และ `.env` ถือว่าเป็นการ \"inspect/touch Hermes files\" ตามกฎของสกิล hermes-permission ครับ\n\n**เจ้านายยืนยันให้ผมดำเนินการ sync กฎระหว่าง Hermes กับ OpenClaw ได้เลยไหมครับ?** 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":423,"output":238,"cacheRead":71680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72341,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778231625688,"responseId":"064cdc4b1e1fe093538505a98c998443"}}
