{"type":"message","id":"5a1ecb64","parentId":"dfd48ef8","timestamp":"2026-05-08T11:08:22.378Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to set up a new protocol where:\n1. Use Qwen2.5-Coder:7b-instruct as the local model (but this needs to be downloaded)\n2. It does two roles: (1) interpreter for sending to cloud, (2) engineer receiving from cloud\n3. Final summary by MiniMax\n\nBut wait - I need to note something important here. The user mentioned \"4060 Ti\" but we just confirmed in the previous message that there's NO GPU in the system. It's running on AMD Ryzen 5 3500X CPU with 23GB RAM, no NVIDIA GPU. \n\nAlso, the current setup uses hermes3:8b as the local model, not Qwen2.5-Coder. The user wants to change this.\n \nLooking at the overall workflow, this new protocol would actually work quite well with the existing MiniMax setup - it would just replace hermes3:8b with Qwen2.5-Coder:7b-instruct as the local model, and the architecture with MiniMax handling final summaries would remain the same.\n\nHowever, I need to flag that Qwen2.5-Coder isn't currently installed, so we'd need to download and run it first before this could actually work. There's also a contradiction between the GPU mention and what we found on the system earlier - I should clarify that. And importantly, I can't actually make changes to the OpenClaw config since the instructions say I should be using config tools rather than direct file edits.\n\nBut actually, looking back at the instructions more carefully - they say to use config tools when possible, but in Step 5 it explicitly says to update openclaw.json. So I should go ahead and save this to MEMORY.md with the note about Qwen2.5-Coder needing to be installed, flag the GPU discrepancy, and use the edit command to update the config.","thinkingSignature":"519b8b4f1b9557545c7ab9b4aaf83127c8ceca7b04538cb487544317ede8d0f5"},{"type":"text","text":"⚠️ **ต้องแก้ไขก่อนบันทึก:**\n\n1. **ไม่มี GPU 4060 Ti** — เช็คเมื่อกี้แล้ว เครื่องไม่มี NVIDIA GPU เลย\n2. **Qwen2.5-Coder ยังไม่ได้ติดตั้ง** — ต้อง pull ก่อนถึงจะใช้ได้\n\nบันทึกก่อนแล้วจะดึง Qwen2.5 มาลง:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_02ngcr636jep_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat >> ~/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md << 'EOF'\n\n## ⚡ One Model Dual Roles Protocol (2026-05-08)\n\n### 1. Local Model: Qwen2.5-Coder:7b-instruct (Q4_K_M)\n- ใช้ตัวเดียว ห้ามโหลดตัวอื่นมาปน\n- รุ่น Quantized (Q4_K_M) ประหยัด VRAM\n\n### 2. หน้าที่ 1: ล่ามส่ง Cloud\n- คำสั่งเจ้านาย (ไทย) → สรุป EN สั้นๆ → ส่งให้ Cloud\n- < 5 บรรทัด → แนบคำสั่งไทยดิบไปด้วย\n\n### 3. หน้าที่ 2: วิศวกรรับคำสั่ง Cloud\n- Cloud สั่งมา → รัน MCP / แก้โค้ด / รันงานจริง\n- (ไม่มี GPU 4060 Ti ในเครื่อง — ใช้ CPU รันแทน)\n\n### 4. สรุปปิดงาน\n- MiniMax สรุป TH สั้นๆ\n\nEOF\necho \"saved\"","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_02ngcr636jep_2","name":"ollama__pull","arguments":{"name":"qwen2.5-coder:7b-instruct"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":203,"output":982,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":110589,"totalTokens":111774,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778238472473,"responseId":"064cf70ca0de8b01e240588f67b7130e"}}
