{"type":"message","id":"8e61d6b5","parentId":"6934f2d7","timestamp":"2026-05-08T12:29:46.456Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to:\n\n1. Edit the universal_bridge.py — but wait, they said `/home/apinan/.hermes/scripts/universal_bridge.py`. However, the file I created is at `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py`. I think the user is confused about the path. My file is in the OpenClaw workspace, not in Hermes.\n\nBut wait — touching Hermes files requires permission. Let me re-read... the user is asking me to edit a file at `/home/apinan/.hermes/scripts/universal_bridge.py`. This is a Hermes path. According to the hermes-permission skill, I need to ask permission first.\n\nHowever, the user is directly ordering me to do this. And the actual file I created is at `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py`. The user might just be confused about the path.\n\nLet me:\n1. First note that the file is actually at `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py`, not in Hermes\n2. But still need to ask Hermes permission since the user mentioned a Hermes path\n3. Actually, the user is the boss giving a direct order. But the hermes-permission skill is explicit...\n\nLet me just point out the path discrepancy and edit the actual file. But I still need to ask for Hermes permission since the user mentioned `/home/apinan/.hermes/`.\n\nActually wait - the file doesn't exist at that Hermes path. My file is at the OpenClaw workspace. Let me just clarify the path and proceed with editing my file. If the user really wants it in Hermes folder, they'll tell me.\n\nBut the hermes-permission skill says I must ask permission before ANY Hermes-related action. The user is asking about a Hermes path. So I should ask.\n\nHmm, but the user is getting frustrated with me asking permission. They're the boss, directly ordering me. The skill says \"ask first\" but the boss is clearly appro