{"type":"message","id":"4334f507","parentId":"5be7722e","timestamp":"2026-05-08T13:27:06.524Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether the system can run all 8 steps of their workflow. Let me be completely honest:\n\nThe universal_bridge.py is a simulation script. It can't actually do the full workflow because it's a standalone Python script, not integrated into OpenClaw's session pipeline.\n\nBut the actual OpenClaw session I'm running in RIGHT NOW does most of these steps. Let me evaluate:\n\n1. [INPUT] - ✅ OpenClaw receives Telegram messages\n2. [LOCAL_GATEWAY] - ✅ OpenClaw gateway pulls messages locally\n3. [LOCAL PREPROCESS] - ✅ Force translate via Local LLM (just proved this works in the bridge test)\n4. [CLOUD ROUTING] - ✅ Bridge just proved it can reach Cloud (MiniMax-M2.7) with the right key\n5. [CLOUD RESPONSE] - ✅ Cloud responded with Action Commands (\"free -h\")\n6. [LOCAL EXECUTION] - ❌ Bridge only plans, doesn't execute. But OpenClaw's exec tool does this.\n7. [FINAL REPORT] - ❌ No automatic MiniMax Thai summarizer in the bridge\n8. [CLEANUP] - ✅ CleanupManager works (Zero Footprint)\n\nThe key insight: the universal_bridge.py script can do steps 1-5 and 8. Steps 6-7 aren't fully implemented in the bridge script.\n\nBut the REAL bridge is this OpenClaw session itself — which CAN do all 8 steps. The universal_bridge.py is just a simulation/proof-of-concept.\n\nLet me be honest and give the boss the real picture. The bridge script partially works. For full integration, the bridge needs to either:\n- Be integrated into OpenClaw as a pipeline\n- Or have steps 6-7 added\n\nBut also, OpenClaw itself already handles most of this natively!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"✓ ตรวจสอบโดยระบบ Local แล้ว (2 บรรทัด)\n\n---\n\n**ตอบตรงๆ:**\n\n| Step | ใน Bridge Script | ใน OpenClaw Session จริง |\n|------|:--:|:--:|\n| 1. INPUT จาก Telegram | ❌ (ไม่มี polling) | ✅ |\n| 2. LOCAL GATEWAY กักไว้ | ❌ (script standalone) | ✅ |\n| 3. FORCE TRANSLATE TH→EN | ✅ (เพิ่งทดสอบผ่าน) | ✅ (ใช้ Ollama MCP) |\n| 4. CLOUD ROUTING | ✅ (ยิง MiniMax สำเร็จ) | ✅ |\n| 5. CLOUD RESPONSE | ✅ (ตอบ Action Commands) | ✅ |\n| 6. LOCAL EXECUTION | ❌ **วางแผนแต่ไม่รันจริง** | ✅ (exec tool) |\n| 7. FINAL REPORT มินิแมกซ์ | ❌ **ไม่มี summarizer** | ⚠️ (ไม่มีอัตโนมัติ) |\n| 8. CLEANUP Zero Footprint | ✅ | ✅ |\n\n---\n\n**สรุป:** Bridge script ผ่าน 5/8 — ติด Step 6 (execution) และ Step 7 (summarizer)\n\n**แต่ใน OpenClaw session นี้ ผ่าน 7/8** — ติดแค่ Step 7 ที่ต้องรัน MiniMax สรุปอัตโนมัติ\n\n**อยากให้ผมเพิ่ม Step 6+7 ใน bridge script ให้ครบ 8/8 เลยไหมครับ?** 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama-pay","model":"deepseek-v4-pro:cloud","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778246749142,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1778246777569"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ec472532","parentId":"4334f507","timestamp":"2026-05-08T13:27:50.745Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"มึงทำให้ Bridge Script (universal_bridge.py) สมบูรณ์ 100% (8/8) ตามนี้:\n\n1. [Add Step 6 - Execution]: เพิ่มระบบให้ Bridge สามารถแกะ Action Commands ออกมา 'รันจริง' ในเครื่องได้ (ใช้ subprocess รัน shell command ที่ Cloud ส่งมา) และเก็บผลลัพธ์ (Output) มาใช้งานต่อ\n\n2. [Add Step 7 - Summarizer]: เมื่อรันเสร็จ ให้ส่งผลลัพธ์ที่ได้ไปให้ Cloud (MiniMax) สรุปเป็นภาษาไทยสั้นๆ ที่เข้าใจง่าย แล้วค่อยส่งกลับมาเป็น Final Report\n\n3. [Test Run]: แก้เสร็จแล้ว ให้ลองรันคำสั่ง 'เช็คอุณหภูมิ CPU และ GPU' โดยต้องผ่าน Step 1 ถึง 8 ให้กูเห็นใน Trace ครั้งเดียวจบ!\n\nกฎเดิม: ห้ามถามเรื่องคีย์ (ใช้ Self-healing ที่มึงทำไว้) และต้องเงียบที่สุด!\""}],"timestamp":1778246870739}}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:1060942816\",\n  \"message_id\": \"7609\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1060942816\",\n  \"sender\": \"▫️\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-05-08 20:27 GMT+7\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"▫️ (1060942816)\",\n  \"id\": \"1060942816\",\n  \"name\": \"▫️\",\n  \"username\": \"robberzaz\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"cfe6a283","parentId":"ec472532","timestamp":"2026-05-08T13:27:50.747Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"9eaf9dc8","parentId":"cfe6a283","timestamp":"2026-05-08T13:29:06.033Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to complete the universal_bridge.py to achieve 8/8 steps:\n\n1. Step 6: Add subprocess execution of Action Commands from Cloud\n2. Step 7: Send results back to Cloud (MiniMax) for Thai summarization\n3. Test: Run \"เช็คอุณหภูมิ CPU และ GPU\" through all 8 steps\n\nLet me edit the file to add these capabilities, making it truly complete.\n\nKey changes needed:\n- Executor: Add `execute_command()` method using subprocess\n- Add `Summarizer` class that sends results to MiniMax for Thai summary\n- Update the main pipeline to include these steps\n- Handle edge cases gracefully","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_gnyb350y","name":"filesystem__edit_file","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"import json\nimport os\nimport re\nimport shutil\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nimport time\nimport urllib.request\nimport urllib.error\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Optional","oldText":"import json\nimport os\nimport shutil\nimport sys\nimport time\nimport urllib.request\nimport urllib.error\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Optional"},{"newText":"class Executor:\n    \"\"\"\n    Local LLM เลือกและรัน tool → EXECUTES FOR REAL\n    Step 6: แกะ Action Commands → รันจริงด้วย subprocess → เก็บ output\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, config: dict, preprocessor: Preprocessor):\n        self.config = config[\"executor\"]\n        self.local = config[\"local\"]\n        self.preprocessor = preprocessor\n    \n    def extract_shell_commands(self, cloud_response: str) -> list[str]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Extract shell commands จาก cloud response\n        จับ: code blocks (```bash), คำสั่งเดี่ยว, หรือ action lines\n        \"\"\"\n        cmds = []\n        text = cloud_response\n        \n        # จับ code blocks ```bash ... ``` หรือ ```sh ... ```\n        for match in re.finditer(r\"```(?:ba?sh|shell)?\\n?(.*?)```\", text, re.DOTALL):\n            block = match.group(1).strip()\n            for line in block.split(\"\\n\"):\n                line = line.strip()\n                if line and not line.startswith(\"#\"):\n                    cmds.append(line)\n        \n        # ถ้าไม่มี code block จับ command lines ทั่วไป\n        if not cmds:\n            for line in text.split(\"\\n\"):\n                line = line.strip()\n                if any(line.startswith(p) for p in [\"free \", \"df \", \"cat \", \"ls \", \"echo \", \"python\", \"nvidia\", \"sensors\", \"grep \", \"ps \"]):\n                    cmds.append(line)\n        \n        return cmds\n    \n    def execute(self, cloud_response: str, timeout: int = 30) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"\n        รัน shell commands จริงในเครื่อง — Step 6\n        Returns: {commands_run, outputs, success}\n        \"\"\"\n        commands = self.extract_shell_commands(cloud_response)\n        if not commands:\n            return {\"commands_run\": [], \"outputs\": [], \"success\": False, \"error\": \"No executable commands found\"}\n        \n        results = []\n        for cmd in commands:\n            try:\n                output = subprocess.check_output(\n                    cmd, shell=True, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n                    timeout=timeout, text=True\n                ).strip()\n                results.append({\"command\": cmd, \"output\": output, \"ok\": True})\n            except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n                results.append({\"command\": cmd, \"output\": \"TIMEOUT\", \"ok\": False})\n            except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e:\n                results.append({\"command\": cmd, \"output\": e.output or str(e), \"ok\": False})\n            except Exception as e:\n                results.append({\"command\": cmd, \"output\": str(e), \"ok\": False})\n        \n        all_ok = all(r[\"ok\"] for r in results)\n        return {\n            \"commands_run\": len(results),\n            \"outputs\": results,\n            \"success\": all_ok,\n            \"raw\": \"\\n\".join(f\"$ {r['command']}\\n{r['output']}\" for r in results)\n        }\n    \n    def plan_execution(self, cloud_response: str) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Local LLM วางแผน execution\"\"\"\n        available = MCP_TOOLS + TERMINAL_TOOLS\n        prompt = f\"\"\"Analyze this Cloud LLM response and plan execution.\n\nResponse:\n{cloud_response}\n\nAvailable tools:\n- MCP: {', '.join(MCP_TOOLS)}\n- Terminal: {', '.join(TERMINAL_TOOLS)}\n\nIf tool execution is needed, specify:\n- tool: which tool to use\n- action: what to do\n\nIf no tool needed, reply \"NO_TOOL_NEEDED\".\"\"\"\n        \n        result = call_llm(\n            self.local[\"base_url\"],\n            self.local[\"model\"],\n            prompt,\n            api_key=self.local[\"api_key\"],\n            system=\"You are an execution planner. Be precise.\",\n            timeout=60\n        )\n        \n        if \"NO_TOOL\" in result.upper():\n            return {\"needs_tool\": False}\n        \n        return {\n            \"needs_tool\": True,\n            \"raw_plan\": result,\n            \"tool\": self.preprocessor.select_tool(cloud_response, available)\n        }","oldText":"class Executor:\n    \"\"\"Local LLM เลือกและรัน tool\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, config: dict, preprocessor: Preprocessor):\n        self.config = config[\"executor\"]\n        self.local = config[\"local\"]\n        self.preprocessor = preprocessor\n    \n    def parse_commands(self, cloud_response: str) -> list[str]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Parse Action Commands ออกจาก cloud response\n        รองรับหลาย format:\n        - \"Action: read_file /path/to/file\"\n        - \"[TOOL] filesystem: read /path\"\n        - หรือแค่คำอธิบายธรรมดา\n        \"\"\"\n        commands = []\n        lines = cloud_response.split(\"\\n\")\n        for line in lines:\n            line = line.strip()\n            if not line:\n                continue\n            # จับ command lines\n            if any(line.startswith(p) for p in [\"Action:\", \"Tool:\", \"[\", \"- \", \"• \"]):\n                commands.append(line)\n        return commands\n    \n    def plan_execution(self, cloud_response: str) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"\n        Local LLM วางแผน execution\n        Returns: {tool: str, action: str, params: dict}\n        \"\"\"\n        available = MCP_TOOLS + TERMINAL_TOOLS\n        prompt = f\"\"\"Analyze this Cloud LLM response and plan execution.\n\nResponse:\n{cloud_response}\n\nAvailable tools:\n- MCP: {', '.join(MCP_TOOLS)}\n- Terminal: {', '.join(TERMINAL_TOOLS)}\n\nIf tool execution is needed, specify:\n- tool: which tool to use\n- action: what to do\n- params: relevant parameters (file paths, etc.)\n\nIf no tool needed, reply \"NO_TOOL_NEEDED\".\"\"\"\n        \n        result = call_llm(\n            self.local[\"base_url\"],\n            self.local[\"model\"],\n            prompt,\n            api_key=self.local[\"api_key\"],\n            system=\"You are an execution planner. Be precise.\",\n            timeout=60\n        )\n        \n        if \"NO_TOOL\" in result.upper():\n            return {\"needs_tool\": False}\n        \n        # Simple parsing\n        return {\n            \"needs_tool\": True,\n            \"raw_plan\": result,\n            \"tool\": self.preprocessor.select_tool(cloud_response, available)\n        }"}],"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama-pay","model":"deepseek-v4-pro:cloud","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778246870747,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1778246891721"}}
