{"type":"compaction","id":"d93d97f3","parentId":"1370989a","timestamp":"2026-05-08T13:49:37.358Z","summary":"## Goal\n1. Build and test a **Universal Agent Bridge** (`universal_bridge.py`) that routes Thai input → Local LLM (translate to EN) → Cloud API → Local execution → Thai summary\n2. Enforce **Zero-Footprint** cleanup (all temp files in `/tmp/bridge/`, auto-delete after pipeline)\n3. Force **100% Local LLM translation** (threshold=0) — every input must go through Local LLM before Cloud, no matter how short\n4. Create **ufo-aiface skill** for OpenClaw based on scripts in `C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Desktop\\Work Auto\\ufo-aiface\\`\n5. Sync rules between Hermes and OpenClaw so both use the same protocols (but remain separate agents)\n6. **NEW**: Implement **Self-Healing Key Vault** — automatic API key recovery from multiple sources without asking user\n7. **NEW**: Achieve **8/8 workflow completion** in `universal_bridge.py`: add Step 6 (real subprocess execution) and Step 7 (MiniMax Thai summarizer of results)\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Boss username: `robberzaz`, Telegram ID: `1060942816`\n- Language: Thai only for communication, English for reasoning/code comments\n- Zero-Footprint: NO files on Desktop, all temp in `/tmp/`, cleanup after every run\n- Hermes-permission skill: Must before touching `~/.hermes/` files\n- Skill lookup rule: If skill not found in `~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/`, check `C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Desktop\\Work Auto\\`\n- Communication style: Short, direct, no questions, use มึง-กู language\n- Every reply must include `🧑🏼‍💻` emoji and verification footer\n- **NEW**: \"ห้ามถามกูเรื่องคีย์\" — NEVER ask boss for API keys; auto-recover or report failure\n- **NEW**: Self-Healing must be silent when successful, only report when all layers fail\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Created `~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-aiface/` skill (SKILL.md, run_aiface.sh, copied scripts from Windows)\n- [x] Created docs: `SOUL.md.txt`, `AGENTS.md.txt`, `MEMORY.txt`, `MCP_SKILLS.txt`, `UNIFIED_RULES.txt`, `CONSOLIDATED_RULES.txt` in `~/.openclaw/workspace/docs/`\n- [x] Saved protocols to MEMORY.md: Hybrid Workflow Protocol, Master Protocol, One Model Dual Roles, Zero-Log Policy, /aiface Safety Gate, Skill Lookup Rule\n- [x] Pulled `qwen2.5-coder:7b-instruct-q4_K_M` (4.7 GB) to Ollama\n- [x] Confirmed GPU: **NVIDIA RTX 4060 Ti 16GB** (via `/mnt/c/Windows/System32/nvidia-smi.exe`)\n- [x] Created `~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py` (17KB+) — 4-stage pipeline: Preprocessor → Router → Executor → Cleanup\n- [x] Created `~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/bridge_config.json`\n- [x] Implemented Zero-Footprint: `/tmp/bridge/` temp dir, `CleanupManager.wipe()` auto-delete, overwrite-only mode\n- [x] Edited Preprocessor `translate()` to force 100% Local LLM translation (threshold=0)\n- [x] Tested bridge pipeline with `\"เช็คแรมหน่อย\"` — Local LLM translated to \"Check the RAM please.\" ✅\n- [x] **Implemented `KeyVault` class** — 4-layer self-healing: ENV → bridge_config.json → openclaw.json → Hermes .env\n- [x] **Updated `Router.__init__`** to use `KeyVault.find()` instead of direct `os.environ.get()`\n- [x] **Tested Self-Healing simulation**: Cleared ENV key → Layer 1-3 failed → Layer 4 (Hermes .env) recovered `sk-79397...` → auto-injected back to ENV ✅\n- [x] **Fixed 401 error**: Initial recovery got DeepSeek key not Ollama-Pay key → corrected key mapping → Cloud (MiniMax-M2.7) responded successfully with `free -h` action command\n- [x] **Full pipeline test passed**: Input → Preprocess → Cloud Routing → Cloud Response → Cleanup — all working with self-healing key\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Adding Step 6 (Local Execution)**: Bridge needs to parse Action Commands from Cloud response, run them via `subprocess`, capture output\n- [ ] **Adding Step 7 (Thai Summarizer)**: Send execution output to MiniMax for Thai-language summary → Final Report\n- [ ] **Full 8/8 test run**: `\"เช็คอุณหภูมิ CPU และ GPU\"` — must show all 8 steps in single trace\n\n### Blocked\n- ~~Cloud API returns 401 because `OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY` is not exported in WSL environment~~ **RESOLVED** — Self-Healing Key Vault now auto-recovers from `~/.hermes/.env`\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **File path**: Bridge lives at `~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py` (NOT `~/.hermes/`)\n- **Temp files**: All in `/tmp/bridge/` (not Desktop, not workspace)\n- **Local model**: `hermes3:8b` is default in config; `qwen2.5-coder:7b-instruct-q4_K_M` also available\n- **Cloud model**: `minimax/MiniMax-M2.7` via `ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com`\n- **Router dual mode**: FILE_MODE (no API key) writes to `/tmp/bridge/input_to_cloud.txt`; HTTP_MODE (with key) sends directly\n- **Force translate**: threshold=0 means EVERY input goes through Local LLM translation, no skipping\n- **Self-Healing Key Vault**: `KeyVault` class with 4-layer fallback — ENV → bridge_config.json → openclaw.json → `~/.hermes/.env`. Silently recovers; only reports \"ระบบกู้คีย์ล้มเหลว\" if ALL layers fail\n- **Key mapping in .env**: Hermes `.env` contains multiple keys (OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY, MINIMAX_API_KEY, DEEPSEEK_API_KEY) — vault checks for the specific key name requested\n- **Bridge vs OpenClaw session**: Bridge script is standalone simulation (currently 5/8), OpenClaw native session does 7/8 — boss wants bridge script to achieve 8/8 independently\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Add `execute_locally()` method to Executor class — parse `bash` code blocks from Cloud response, run via `subprocess.run()`, capture stdout/stderr\n2. Add `summarize_thai()` method — send execution output to MiniMax API with prompt \"สรุปเป็นภาษาไทยสั้นๆ\", return Thai text\n3. Wire Step 6 → Step 7 in main pipeline: execution output feeds into summarizer\n4. Test full 8/8 run with input `\"เช็คอุณหภูมิ CPU และ GPU\"` — verify all steps in trace\n5. Ensure self-healing key works end-to-end (no key questions)\n\n## Critical Context\n- System specs: AMD Ryzen 5 3500X, 23GB RAM, RTX 4060 Ti 16GB, WSL2 Ubuntu, Python 3.12.3\n- Ollama local models: `hermes3:8b` (4.6GB), `qwen2.5-coder:7b-instruct-q4_K_M` (4.7GB), `nomic-embed-text`\n- nvidia-smi accessible via `/mnt/c/Windows/System32/nvidia-smi.exe` (not directly in WSL)\n- OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY exists in `~/.hermes/.env` but not exported in WSL shell — **KeyVault solves this**\n- MCP servers: socraticode, puppeteer, sequential-thinking, filesystem, ollama\n- Plugin skills: browser-automation, create-face-portrait, hermes-permission, socraticode-code, telegram-word-relay, ufo-gpt-image-gen, ufo-windows-automation, **ufo-aiface**\n- Cloud endpoint: `https://ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com/v1/chat/completions` with model `MiniMax-M2.7`\n- Successful Cloud response format: Returns analysis text + Action Commands in markdown `bash` code blocks (e.g., `free -h`)\n- Current bridge pipeline flow: `main()` → `Preprocessor.translate()` → `Router.send_to_cloud()` → `Executor` (plans only) → `CleanupManager.wipe()`\n\n<read-files>\n/home/apinan/.hermes/SOUL.md\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/hermes-permission/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-aiface/SKILL.md\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-aiface/run_aiface.sh\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/docs/CONSOLIDATED_RULES.txt\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/docs/MCP_SKILLS.txt\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/docs/UNIFIED_RULES.txt\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/TG_SUCCESS.txt\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/bridge_config.json\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/toxic_detection_sim.py\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"cfe6a283","tokensBefore":0,"details":{"readFiles":["/home/apinan/.hermes/SOUL.md","/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/hermes-permission/SKILL.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-aiface/SKILL.md","/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-aiface/run_aiface.sh","/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/docs/CONSOLIDATED_RULES.txt","/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/docs/MCP_SKILLS.txt","/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/docs/UNIFIED_RULES.txt","/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/TG_SUCCESS.txt","/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/bridge_config.json","/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py","/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/toxic_detection_sim.py"]},"fromHook":false}
{"type":"message","id":"678b1763","parentId":"d93d97f3","timestamp":"2026-05-08T13:49:38.612Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"มึงปรับจูน UNIT 2 (The Architect) และ UNIT 3 (The Coder) เพิ่มเติมตามนี้:\n\n1. [MCP Discovery]: ก่อนเริ่มวางแผน ให้มึงรวบรวมรายชื่อ MCP Tools (Model Context Protocol) ทั้งหมดที่มีอยู่ในระบบของกู แล้วส่งให้ UNIT 2 (สมองหลัก) รับรู้เป็นบริบทพื้นฐาน\n\n2. [Architect Instruction]: สั่งให้ UNIT 2 ต้องวิเคราะห์และอธิบายออกมาด้วยว่า 'งานนี้ควรใช้ MCP ตัวไหน' เพื่อให้มีประสิทธิภาพสูงสุด และต้องระบุชื่อ Tool ในแผนงานให้ชัดเจน\n\n3. [Effective Execution]: แก้ให้ UNIT 3 (นักเขียนโค้ด) สามารถเรียกใช้งาน MCP Tools เหล่านั้นได้จริงตามที่สมองหลักสั่งมา โดยต้องรันคำสั่งผ่าน Protocol ที่ถูกต้อง (ไม่ลงแรงเสียเปล่า)\n\n4. [Trace Update]: ในหน้า Report ให้มึงเพิ่มบรรทัด 'Selected MCP Tools: [ชื่อเครื่องมือ]' เพื่อให้กูเห็นว่ามึงเลือกใช้อาวุธได้ถูกชิ้นไหม\n\nลองทดสอบด้วยการสั่ง: 'กูอยากรู้ว่าช่วงนี้ในโฟลเดอร์งานของกูมีไฟล์ไหนใหญ่ผิดปกติบ้าง และช่วยหาข้อมูลในเน็ตให้หน่อยว่าโปรแกรมอะไรชอบสร้างไฟล์ขยะพวกนี้' (ทดสอบการใช้ MCP File System + Search พร้อมกัน)!\""}],"timestamp":1778248178610}}
