{"type":"message","id":"b365da7b","parentId":"e740b5a5","timestamp":"2026-05-08T13:58:02.272Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking \"ยังไง\" which means \"how?\" or \"what's going on?\" - they want me to proceed with the MCP integration I described. Let me just do it directly - rewrite the universal_bridge.py with MCP support integrated.\n\nLet me plan this:\n\n1. Add MCP Discovery - scan the system for available MCP tools\n2. Update Architect instructions to include MCP tool selection\n3. Update Coder to actually call MCP tools (or generate commands that use them)\n4. Add \"Selected MCP Tools\" to trace\n\nSince we're in a WSL environment with access to MCP tools like socraticode, puppeteer, filesystem, etc., I can:\n- Use `codebase_list_projects` to discover available projects\n- The actual MCP tools available to this session are: socraticode__*, puppeteer__*, filesystem__*, ollama__*, sequential-thinking__*, sessions_*, web_search, web_fetch, etc.\n\nFor the bridge script, MCP execution would need to:\n- Parse MCP tool names from the plan\n- Call them via OpenAI-compatible API or subprocess\n- Since the bridge is a standalone Python script, it can use `subprocess` to call tools, or make API calls directly\n\nActually, the bridge script runs independently. MCP tools are exposed through the OpenClaw/MCP server protocol. The bridge can't directly call them unless:\n1. It calls them via the MCP server's HTTP endpoint\n2. Or it simulates them with equivalent shell commands\n\nFor the filesystem tools, the bridge can use Python's built-in `os` and `Path` libraries. For web search, it can use `urllib` or `requests`.\n\nLet me take a practical approach:\n- MCP Discovery: List available tools from a known registry/config\n- Architect: Include MCP tool recommendations in the plan\n- Coder: Map MCP tool references to actual Python code that executes equivalent functionality\n- Trace: Show which MCP tools were selected\n\nLet me rewrite the bridge with this integrated.\n\nActually, let me think about this more practically. The bridge currently uses subprocess for execution. MCP tools like `filesystem__search_files`, `web_search`, `web_fetch` can be emulated:\n\n- `filesystem__search_files` → `find` command or Python `Path.glob()`\n- `web_search` → `curl` to a search API\n- `web_fetch` → `curl` or `wget` + text extraction\n- `filesystem__read_file` → `cat` or Python file reading\n\nFor a clean implementation:\n1. I'll create an MCP registry in the bridge\n2. Architect gets the list of MCP tools as context\n3. Coder maps MCP tool names to actual Python functions\n4. Execute them\n\nLet me write thisnow.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5yq07z10","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\n╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n║         UNIVERSAL AGENT BRIDGE — 4-UNIT + MCP INTEGRATION          ║\n║                                                                    ║\n║  UNIT 1 — TRANSLATOR  (Local Qwen-2.5)      TH→EN                 ║\n║  UNIT 2 — ARCHITECT   (Cloud, swappable)    Analyze + MCP Select  ║\n║  UNIT 3 — CODER       (Local + MCP Exec)    Code & Execute        ║\n║  UNIT 4 — REPORTER    (MiniMax-M2.7)        Thai Summary           ║\n║                                                                    ║\n║  🧰 MCP: Auto-Discovery + Real Execution + Tool Trace             ║\n║  🔑 Self-Healing Key Vault | 🗑️ Zero Footprint                    ║\n╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport os\nimport re\nimport shutil\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nimport time\nimport urllib.request\nimport urllib.error\nimport fnmatch\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# CONSTANTS\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nBRIDGE_TMP = \"/tmp/bridge\"\nBRIDGE_INPUT = f\"{BRIDGE_TMP}/input_to_cloud.txt\"\n\n\ndef _ensure_tmp():\n    os.makedirs(BRIDGE_TMP, exist_ok=True)\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# MCP TOOL REGISTRY — รายชื่อ MCP tools ทั้งหมด + คำอธิบาย\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nMCP_REGISTRY = {\n    # ── Filesystem Tools ──\n    \"filesystem__list_directory\": {\n        \"desc\": \"List files/dirs in a path (like 'ls')\",\n        \"params\": [\"path\"],\n        \"category\": \"filesystem\",\n        \"native\": True\n    },\n    \"filesystem__directory_tree\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Recursive tree view of a directory\",\n        \"params\": [\"path\", \"excludePatterns\"],\n        \"category\": \"filesystem\",\n        \"native\": True\n    },\n    \"filesystem__list_directory_with_sizes\": {\n        \"desc\": \"List files with sizes, sortable by name/size\",\n        \"params\": [\"path\", \"sortBy\"],\n        \"category\": \"filesystem\",\n        \"native\": True\n    },\n    \"filesystem__search_files\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Search recursively by glob pattern like '*.log', '**/*.py'\",\n        \"params\": [\"path\", \"pattern\", \"excludePatterns\"],\n        \"category\": \"filesystem\",\n        \"native\": True\n    },\n    \"filesystem__read_text_file\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Read text file content (supports head/tail)\",\n        \"params\": [\"path\", \"head\", \"tail\"],\n        \"category\": \"filesystem\",\n        \"native\": True\n    },\n    \"filesystem__get_file_info\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Get file metadata: size, modified time, permissions\",\n        \"params\": [\"path\"],\n        \"category\": \"filesystem\",\n        \"native\": True\n    },\n    \"filesystem__read_multiple_files\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Read multiple files at once\",\n        \"params\": [\"paths\"],\n        \"category\": \"filesystem\",\n        \"native\": True\n    },\n\n    # ── Web Tools ──\n    \"web_search\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Search the web with query, supports language/country filters\",\n        \"params\": [\"query\", \"count\", \"language\", \"freshness\"],\n        \"category\": \"web\",\n        \"native\": False,\n        \"shell_hint\": \"python3 -c '... urllib web search ...'\"\n    },\n    \"web_fetch\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Fetch a URL and extract readable content (markdown/text)\",\n        \"params\": [\"url\", \"extractMode\", \"maxChars\"],\n        \"category\": \"web\",\n        \"native\": False,\n        \"shell_hint\": \"curl -sL URL | python3 -c '... text extraction ...'\"\n    },\n\n    # ── Code Analysis (SocratiCode) ──\n    \"socraticode__codebase_search\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Semantic search across indexed codebase\",\n        \"params\": [\"query\", \"projectPath\", \"limit\"],\n        \"category\": \"code\",\n        \"native\": False,\n        \"shell_hint\": \"N/A (requires MCP server)\"\n    },\n    \"socraticode__codebase_status\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Check indexing status of a project\",\n        \"params\": [\"projectPath\"],\n        \"category\": \"code\",\n        \"native\": False,\n        \"shell_hint\": \"N/A (requires MCP server)\"\n    },\n    \"socraticode__codebase_impact\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Blast radius analysis for a file/symbol\",\n        \"params\": [\"target\", \"projectPath\"],\n        \"category\": \"code\",\n        \"native\": False,\n        \"shell_hint\": \"N/A (requires MCP server)\"\n    },\n\n    # ── Ollama ──\n    \"ollama__list\": {\n        \"desc\": \"List all Ollama models installed locally\",\n        \"params\": [],\n        \"category\": \"ai\",\n        \"native\": True\n    },\n    \"ollama__chat_completion\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Send a chat completion to any Ollama model\",\n        \"params\": [\"model\", \"messages\", \"temperature\"],\n        \"category\": \"ai\",\n        \"native\": False,\n        \"shell_hint\": \"curl localhost:11434/v1/chat/completions ...\"\n    },\n\n    # ── Shell/System ──\n    \"terminal__bash\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Execute any bash shell command\",\n        \"params\": [\"command\", \"timeout\"],\n        \"category\": \"system\",\n        \"native\": True\n    },\n    \"terminal__python\": {\n        \"desc\": \"Execute Python one-liner or script\",\n        \"params\": [\"code\", \"args\"],\n        \"category\": \"system\",\n        \"native\": True\n    },\n}\n\n\ndef discover_mcp_tools() -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    MCP Discovery: รวบรวม MCP tools ทั้งหมดที่มีในระบบ\n    เช็คทั้งจาก registry + ตรวจสอบว่าตัวไหนใช้งานได้จริง\n    \"\"\"\n    available = {}\n\n    for name, info in MCP_REGISTRY.items():\n        status = \"ready\" if _check_tool_available(name) else \"unavailable\"\n        available[name] = {\n            \"description\": info[\"desc\"],\n            \"category\": info[\"category\"],\n            \"status\": status,\n            \"native\": info.get(\"native\", False),\n            \"params\": info[\"params\"],\n        }\n\n    return available\n\n\ndef _check_tool_available(tool_name: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"เช็คว่า tool นี้ใช้ได้ในระบบปัจจุบันไหม\"\"\"\n    category = MCP_REGISTRY.get(tool_name, {}).get(\"category\", \"\")\n\n    if category == \"filesystem\":\n        return True  # filesystem ใช้ได้ตลอด\n    if category == \"web\":\n        # เช็คว่า curl ใช้ได้ไหม\n        try:\n            subprocess.run([\"which\", \"curl\"], capture_output=True, timeout=5)\n            return True\n        except Exception:\n            return False\n    if category == \"code\":\n        # เช็ค SocratiCode (Qdrant + Ollama)\n        try:\n            result = subprocess.run(\n                [\"curl\", \"-s\", \"--max-time\", \"3\", \"http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags\"],\n                capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=8\n            )\n            return \"models\" in result.stdout\n        except Exception:\n            return False\n    if category == \"ai\":\n        try:\n            result = subprocess.run(\n                [\"curl\", \"-s\", \"--max-time\", \"3\", \"http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags\"],\n                capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=8\n            )\n            return \"models\" in result.stdout\n        except Exception:\n            return False\n    if category == \"system\":\n        return True  # bash/python ใช้ได้ตลอด\n\n    return False\n\n\ndef format_mcp_context(available_tools: dict) -> str:\n    \"\"\"แปลงรายชื่อ MCP tools เป็น context ให้ Architect อ่าน\"\"\"\n    lines = [\"AVAILABLE MCP TOOLS (you MUST reference these in your plan):\"]\n\n    by_category = {}\n    for name, info in available_tools.items():\n        cat = info[\"category\"]\n        by_category.setdefault(cat, []).append((name, info))\n\n    for cat, tools in sorted(by_category.items()):\n        lines.append(f\"\\n  [{cat.upper()}]\")\n        for name, info in tools:\n            icon = \"✅\" if info[\"status\"] == \"ready\" else \"⛔\"\n            native_tag = \" [NATIVE]\" if info[\"native\"] else \"\"\n            lines.append(f\"    {icon} {name}{native_tag}\")\n            lines.append(f\"       {info['description']}\")\n            if info[\"params\"]:\n                lines.append(f\"       Params: {', '.join(info['params'])}\")\n\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# SELF-HEALING KEY VAULT\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nclass KeyVault:\n    \"\"\"\n    4-Layer Self-Healing:\n      ENV → bridge_config.json → openclaw.json → ~/.hermes/.env\n    \"\"\"\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def find(key_name: str = \"OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY\") -> Optional[str]:\n        # Layer 1: ENV\n        val = os.environ.get(key_name, \"\")\n        if val and len(val) > 10:\n            return val\n\n        # Layer 2: bridge_config.json\n        cfg_path = Path(\"~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/bridge_config.json\").expanduser()\n        if cfg_path.exists():\n            try:\n                cfg = json.loads(cfg_path.read_text())\n                for path in [\"cloud.api_key\", \"architect.api_key\", \"reporter.api_key\"]:\n                    v = KeyVault._json_path(cfg, path)\n                    if v and len(v) > 10:\n                        os.environ[key_name] = v\n                        return v\n            except Exception:\n                pass\n\n        # Layer 3: openclaw.json\n        oc_path = Path(\"~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\").expanduser()\n        if oc_path.exists():\n            try:\n                data = json.loads(oc_path.read_text())\n                found = KeyVault._deep_search(\n                    data, [\"api_key\", \"apiKey\", \"key\", \"token\"])\n                if found:\n                    os.environ[key_name] = found\n                    return found\n            except Exception:\n                pass\n\n        # Layer 4: Hermes .env\n        hermes_env = Path(\"~/.hermes/.env\").expanduser()\n        if hermes_env.exists():\n            try:\n                for line in hermes_env.read_text().split(\"\\n\"):\n                    line = line.strip()\n                    if line.startswith(\"#\") or \"=\" not in line:\n                        continue\n                    k, v = line.split(\"=\", 1)\n                    k, v = k.strip(), v.strip().strip('\"\\'').strip(\"'\")\n                    if k == key_name and len(v) > 10:\n                        os.environ[key_name] = v\n                        return v\n            except Exception:\n                pass\n\n        return None\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _json_path(obj, dotpath: str) -> Optional[str]:\n        for key in dotpath.split(\".\"):\n            if isinstance(obj, dict):\n                obj = obj.get(key)\n            else:\n                return None\n        return obj if isinstance(obj, str) else None\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _deep_search(obj, target_keys: list) -> Optional[str]:\n        if isinstance(obj, str) and len(obj) > 15:\n            return obj\n        if isinstance(obj, dict):\n            for k, v in obj.items():\n                if k in target_keys and isinstance(v, str) and len(v) > 10:\n                    return v\n                r = KeyVault._deep_search(v, target_keys)\n                if r:\n                    return r\n        elif isinstance(obj, list):\n            for item in obj:\n                r = KeyVault._deep_search(item, target_keys)\n                if r:\n                    return r\n        return None\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def get() -> str:\n        return KeyVault.find(\"OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY\") or \"\"\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# LLM CALL HELPER\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\ndef call_llm(base_url: str, model: str, prompt: str, *,\n             api_key: str = \"\", system: str = \"\",\n             temperature: float = 0.3, timeout: int = 90) -> str:\n    body = {\n        \"model\": model,\n        \"messages\": [],\n        \"temperature\": temperature,\n    }\n    if system:\n        body[\"messages\"].append({\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system})\n    body[\"messages\"].append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt})\n\n    data = json.dumps(body).encode(\"utf-8\")\n    headers = {\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}\n    if api_key:\n        headers[\"Authorization\"] = f\"Bearer {api_key}\"\n\n    req = urllib.request.Request(\n        f\"{base_url}/chat/completions\", data=data, headers=headers)\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=timeout) as resp:\n            raw = json.loads(resp.read().decode())\n            content = raw[\"choices\"][0][\"message\"][\"content\"]\n            return content.strip() if content else \"\"\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        body_snip = e.read().decode(errors=\"replace\")[:200]\n        return f\"[HTTP ERROR {e.code}]: {body_snip}\"\n    except Exception as e:\n        return f\"[ERROR]: {e}\"\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# CONFIGURATION\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nDEFAULT_CONFIG = {\n    \"units\": {\n        \"translator\": {\n            \"model\": \"qwen2.5-coder:7b-instruct-q4_K_M\",\n            \"base_url\": \"http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1\",\n            \"api_key\": \"ollama\",\n            \"description\": \"UNIT 1 — TH→EN\"\n        },\n        \"architect\": {\n            \"model\": \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\",\n            \"base_url\": \"https://ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com/api/v1\",\n            \"api_key_env\": \"OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY\",\n            \"timeout\": 120,\n            \"description\": \"UNIT 2 — Analyze + MCP Select\"\n        },\n        \"coder\": {\n            \"model\": \"qwen2.5-coder:7b-instruct-q4_K_M\",\n            \"base_url\": \"http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1\",\n            \"api_key\": \"ollama\",\n            \"timeout\": 60,\n            \"exec_timeout\": 45,\n            \"description\": \"UNIT 3 — Code + Execute + MCP\"\n        },\n        \"reporter\": {\n            \"model\": \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\",\n            \"base_url\": \"https://ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com/api/v1\",\n            \"api_key_env\": \"OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY\",\n            \"timeout\": 120,\n            \"description\": \"UNIT 4 — Thai Summary\"\n        }\n    },\n    \"global\": {\n        \"zero_footprint\": True,\n        \"trace\": True,\n        \"mcp_discovery\": True,\n        \"force_translate_threshold\": 0\n    }\n}\n\n\ndef load_config(path: str = \"~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/bridge_config.json\") -> dict:\n    p = Path(path).expanduser()\n    if p.exists():\n        try:\n            return json.loads(p.read_text())\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n    return DEFAULT_CONFIG\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# UNIT 1 — TRANSLATOR\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nclass Translator:\n    \"\"\"UNIT 1: Thai → English via Local Qwen-2.5\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, config: dict):\n        self.cfg = config[\"units\"][\"translator\"]\n        self.global_cfg = config[\"global\"]\n\n    def translate(self, thai_input: str) -> tuple[str, bool]:\n        threshold = self.global_cfg.get(\"force_translate_threshold\", 0)\n        if len(thai_input) < threshold:\n            return thai_input, False\n\n        prompt = f\"\"\"Translate this Thai message to SHORT English.\nFocus on the core intent and key details. Maximum 3 sentences.\n\nThai: {thai_input}\n\nEnglish translation:\"\"\"\n\n        result = call_llm(\n            self.cfg[\"base_url\"], self.cfg[\"model\"], prompt,\n            api_key=self.cfg.get(\"api_key\", \"ollama\"),\n            system=\"You translate Thai to concise English. Reply with translation only.\",\n            timeout=90\n        )\n\n        if result.startswith(\"[ERROR]\") or result.startswith(\"[HTTP\"):\n            return thai_input[:200] + \"…\", False\n\n        return result.strip(), True\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# UNIT 2 — ARCHITECT (MCP-Aware)\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nclass Architect:\n    \"\"\"\n    UNIT 2: สมองหลัก — รับ MCP context → วิเคราะห์ → เลือก MCP tools → วางแผน\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, config: dict):\n        self.cfg = config[\"units\"][\"architect\"]\n        self.global_cfg = config[\"global\"]\n        self.api_key = KeyVault.find(\n            self.cfg.get(\"api_key_env\", \"OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY\")) or \"\"\n        self.mcp_context = \"\"\n        self.selected_tools = []\n\n    def discover_and_prepare(self):\n        \"\"\"MCP Discovery: รวบรวม tools ให้ Architect ใช้\"\"\"\n        available = discover_mcp_tools()\n        self.mcp_context = format_mcp_context(available)\n        return available\n\n    def plan(self, english_input: str, mcp_available: dict = None) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Analyze + MCP tool selection + execution plan\"\"\"\n\n        if mcp_available is None:\n            mcp_available = discover_mcp_tools()\n            self.mcp_context = format_mcp_context(mcp_available)\n\n        prompt = f\"\"\"[ROLE: SYSTEM ARCHITECT]\nYou analyze problems and create execution plans. You SELECT the right MCP tools.\n\n{mcp_context or self.mcp_context}\n\n──────────────────────────────────────\nUSER REQUEST (translated from Thai):\n\"{english_input}\"\n──────────────────────────────────────\n\nYour response MUST follow this structure:\n\n## MCP TOOL SELECTION\nFor each relevant MCP tool, explain:\n- **Tool**: <exact tool name from the list above>\n- **Why**: why this tool is ideal for the task\n- **How**: specific params/usage\n\n## EXECUTION PLAN\nStep-by-step, with commands in ```bash blocks.\n\nCRITICAL RULES:\n1. ALWAYS reference tools by their EXACT name from the available list\n2. Use ✅ (ready) tools first; ⛔ tools are unavailable\n3. Put ALL executable commands in ```bash code blocks\n4. For web_search: use ```bash blocks with curl commands\n5. For filesystem: use ```bash blocks with find/du/ls commands\n\"\"\"\n\n        response = call_llm(\n            self.cfg[\"base_url\"], self.cfg[\"model\"], prompt,\n            api_key=***\n            system=\"System Architect: analyze + select MCP tools + plan execution. Always reference exact tool names.\",\n            timeout=self.cfg.get(\"timeout\", 120)\n        )\n\n        # Extract MCP tool names from the plan\n        self.selected_tools = self._extract_selected_tools(\n            response, mcp_available)\n\n        return {\n            \"raw\": response,\n            \"success\": not response.startswith(\"[ERROR]\") and not response.startswith(\"[HTTP\"),\n            \"model_used\": self.cfg[\"model\"],\n            \"selected_mcp_tools\": self.selected_tools,\n        }\n\n    def _extract_selected_tools(self, plan_text: str, available: dict) -> list[str]:\n        \"\"\"Parse plan text to find which MCP tools were selected\"\"\"\n        found = []\n        plan_lower = plan_text.lower()\n        for tool_name in available:\n            if tool_name.lower() in plan_lower:\n                cat = available[tool_name][\"category\"]\n                found.append(f\"{tool_name} [{cat}]\")\n        return found if found else [\"terminal__bash [system]\"]\n\n    @property\n    def active_model(self) -> str:\n        return self.cfg[\"model\"]\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# UNIT 3 — CODER (MCP Executor)\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nclass Coder:\n    \"\"\"\n    UNIT 3: รับแผน → Execute shell commands + MCP tool emulation\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, config: dict):\n        self.cfg = config[\"units\"][\"coder\"]\n        self.global_cfg = config[\"global\"]\n\n    # ── Command Extraction ──\n\n    def extract_commands(self, plan_text: str) -> list[dict]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Extract executable items from plan:\n        - Shell commands from ```bash blocks\n        - MCP tool references (for native execution)\n        Returns list of {\"type\": \"shell\"|\"mcp\", \"content\": ...}\n        \"\"\"\n        items = []\n\n        # Extract bash/shell code blocks\n        for match in re.finditer(\n                r\"```(?:ba?sh|shell)?\\n?(.*?)```\", plan_text, re.DOTALL):\n            for line in match.group(1).strip().split(\"\\n\"):\n                line = line.strip()\n                if line and not line.startswith(\"#\") and not line.startswith(\"//\"):\n                    items.append({\"type\": \"shell\", \"command\": line})\n\n        # Extract MCP tool references from plan text\n        for match in re.finditer(\n                r'(?:\\*\\*Tool\\*\\*:\\s*|tool[:\\s]+|use\\s+)(filesystem__\\w+|web_\\w+|ollama__\\w+|socraticode__\\w+|terminal__\\w+)',\n                plan_text, re.IGNORECASE):\n            tool_name = match.group(1)\n            if not any(i.get(\"mcp_tool\") == tool_name for i in items):\n                items.append({\"type\": \"mcp\", \"mcp_tool\": tool_name, \"params\": {}})\n\n        # Fallback: scan for known command prefixes\n        if not items:\n            for line in plan_text.split(\"\\n\"):\n                line = line.strip()\n                if any(line.startswith(p) for p in [\n                    \"free \", \"df \", \"cat \", \"ls \", \"echo \", \"python\",\n                    \"nvidia\", \"sensors\", \"grep \", \"ps \", \"docker\",\n                    \"systemctl\", \"curl \", \"wget \", \"git \", \"find \",\n                    \"du \", \"wc \", \"sort \", \"head \", \"tail \"\n                ]):\n                    items.append({\"type\": \"shell\", \"command\": line})\n\n        return items\n\n    # ── MCP Native Execution ──\n\n    def _exec_mcp_filesystem(self, tool_name: str, params: dict) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Execute filesystem MCP tools natively in Python\"\"\"\n        path = params.get(\"path\", \".\")\n\n        if tool_name == \"filesystem__list_directory\":\n            try:\n                entries = []\n                for f in sorted(Path(path).iterdir()):\n                    tag = \"[DIR]\" if f.is_dir() else \"[FILE]\"\n                    entries.append(f\"{tag} {f.name}\")\n                return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": \"\\n\".join(entries) or \"(empty)\"}\n            except Exception as e:\n                return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": str(e)}\n\n        elif tool_name == \"filesystem__list_directory_with_sizes\":\n            try:\n                entries = []\n                for f in sorted(Path(path).iterdir()):\n                    size = f.stat().st_size if f.is_file() else 0\n                    tag = \"[DIR]\" if f.is_dir() else \"[FILE]\"\n                    if size >= 1_000_000_000:\n                        size_str = f\"{size/1_000_000_000:.1f}GB\"\n                    elif size >= 1_000_000:\n                        size_str = f\"{size/1_000_000:.1f}MB\"\n                    elif size >= 1_000:\n                        size_str = f\"{size/1000:.1f}KB\"\n                    else:\n                        size_str = f\"{size}B\"\n                    entries.append(f\"{tag} {f.name} ({size_str})\")\n                return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": \"\\n\".join(entries) or \"(empty)\"}\n            except Exception as e:\n                return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": str(e)}\n\n        elif tool_name == \"filesystem__search_files\":\n            pattern = params.get(\"pattern\", \"*\")\n            try:\n                matched = []\n                base = Path(path)\n                for f in base.rglob(pattern):\n                    if f.is_file():\n                        size = f.stat().st_size\n                        if size >= 1_000_000:\n                            size_str = f\"{size/1_000_000:.1f}MB\"\n                        elif size >= 1_000:\n                            size_str = f\"{size/1000:.1f}KB\"\n                        else:\n                            size_str = f\"{size}B\"\n                        matched.append(\n                            f\"{f.relative_to(base)} ({size_str}, {datetime.fromtimestamp(f.stat().st_mtime).strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')})\")\n                if not matched:\n                    return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": f\"No files match '{pattern}'\"}\n                return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": \"\\n\".join(matched[:50]) + (f\"\\n... and {len(matched)-50} more\" if len(matched) > 50 else \"\")}\n            except Exception as e:\n                return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": str(e)}\n\n        elif tool_name == \"filesystem__directory_tree\":\n            try:\n                lines = []\n                base = Path(path)\n\n                def _tree(p: Path, prefix: str = \"\"):\n                    entries = sorted(p.iterdir())\n                    for i, e in enumerate(entries):\n                        is_last = i == len(entries) - 1\n                        connector = \"└── \" if is_last else \"├── \"\n                        if e.is_dir():\n                            lines.append(f\"{prefix}{connector}{e.name}/\")\n                            _tree(e, prefix +\n                                  (\"    \" if is_last else \"│   \"))\n                        else:\n                            size = e.stat().st_size\n                            if size >= 1_000_000:\n                                s = f\"{size/1_000_000:.1f}MB\"\n                            elif size >= 1_000:\n                                s = f\"{size/1000:.1f}KB\"\n                            else:\n                                s = f\"{size}B\"\n                            lines.append(\n                                f\"{prefix}{connector}{e.name} ({s})\")\n\n                lines.append(f\"{base.name}/\")\n                _tree(base)\n                return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": \"\\n\".join(lines[:80])}\n            except Exception as e:\n                return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": str(e)}\n\n        elif tool_name == \"filesystem__read_text_file\":\n            try:\n                p = Path(path)\n                content = p.read_text()\n                head = params.get(\"head\")\n                tail = params.get(\"tail\")\n                if head:\n                    content = \"\\n\".join(content.split(\"\\n\")[:head])\n                elif tail:\n                    content = \"\\n\".join(content.split(\"\\n\")[-tail:])\n                if len(content) > 3000:\n                    content = content[:3000] + \"\\n…(trimmed)\"\n                return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": content}\n            except Exception as e:\n                return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": str(e)}\n\n        elif tool_name == \"filesystem__get_file_info\":\n            try:\n                p = Path(path)\n                st = p.stat()\n                info = f\"\"\"\nName: {p.name}\nPath: {p.absolute()}\nSize: {st.st_size:,} bytes ({st.st_size/1_000_000:.1f}MB)\nType: {\"Directory\" if p.is_dir() else \"File\"}\nModified: {datetime.fromtimestamp(st.st_mtime).strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}\nCreated:  {datetime.fromtimestamp(st.st_ctime).strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}\nPermissions: {oct(st.st_mode)[-3:]}\n\"\"\"\n                return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": info.strip()}\n            except Exception as e:\n                return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": str(e)}\n\n        elif tool_name == \"filesystem__read_multiple_files\":\n            paths = params.get(\"paths\", [])\n            outputs = []\n            for fp in paths:\n                try:\n                    content = Path(fp).read_text()\n                    outputs.append(f\"─── {fp} ───\\n{content[:500]}\")\n                except Exception as e:\n                    outputs.append(f\"─── {fp} ───\\n[ERROR: {e}]\")\n            return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": \"\\n\\n\".join(outputs)}\n\n        return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": f\"Unknown MCP tool: {tool_name}\"}\n\n    def _exec_mcp_web(self, tool_name: str, params: dict) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Execute web MCP tools\"\"\"\n        if tool_name == \"web_search\":\n            query = params.get(\"query\", \"\")\n            if not query:\n                return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": \"No search query provided\"}\n            # Use DuckDuckGo lite as search backend (no API key needed)\n            try:\n                search_url = f\"https://lite.duckduckgo.com/lite/?q={urllib.request.quote(query)}\"\n                req = urllib.request.Request(search_url, headers={\n                    \"User-Agent\": \"Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64) AppleWebKit/537.36\"})\n                with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=20) as resp:\n                    html = resp.read().decode(errors=\"replace\")\n                # Simple extraction of result snippets\n                import html as html_mod\n                text = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', '\\n', html)\n                text = html_mod.unescape(text)\n                lines = [l.strip()\n                         for l in text.split(\"\\n\") if len(l.strip()) > 30]\n                return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": \"\\n\".join(lines[:20]) or \"No results extracted\"}\n            except Exception as e:\n                return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": f\"Search failed: {e}\"}\n\n        elif tool_name == \"web_fetch\":\n            url = params.get(\"url\", \"\")\n            if not url:\n                return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": \"No URL provided\"}\n            try:\n                req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={\n                    \"User-Agent\": \"Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; Bridge/1.0)\"})\n                with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=30) as resp:\n                    raw = resp.read().decode(errors=\"replace\")\n                # Strip HTML tags\n                text = re.sub(r'<script[^>]*>.*?</script>',\n                              '', raw, flags=re.DOTALL)\n                text = re.sub(r'<style[^>]*>.*?</style>',\n                              '', text, flags=re.DOTALL)\n                text = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', text)\n                text = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text).strip()\n                max_chars = params.get(\"maxChars\", 3000)\n                if len(text) > max_chars:\n                    text = text[:max_chars] + \"…(trimmed)\"\n                return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": text[:5000]}\n            except Exception as e:\n                return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": f\"Fetch failed: {e}\"}\n\n        return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": f\"Unknown web tool: {tool_name}\"}\n\n    def _exec_mcp_ai(self, tool_name: str, params: dict) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Execute AI/LLM MCP tools\"\"\"\n        if tool_name == \"ollama__list\":\n            try:\n                result = subprocess.check_output(\n                    [\"curl\", \"-s\", \"http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags\"],\n                    timeout=10, text=True\n                )\n                data = json.loads(result)\n                models = []\n                for m in data.get(\"models\", []):\n                    size_gb = m.get(\"size\", 0) / 1_000_000_000\n                    models.append(f\"  - {m['name']} ({size_gb:.1f}GB)\")\n                return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": \"Installed Ollama models:\\n\" + \"\\n\".join(models)}\n            except Exception as e:\n                return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": str(e)}\n\n        if tool_name == \"ollama__chat_completion\":\n            model = params.get(\"model\", self.cfg[\"model\"])\n            messages = params.get(\"messages\", [])\n            try:\n                result = call_llm(\n                    \"http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1\", model,\n                    messages[-1][\"content\"] if messages else \"Hello\",\n                    system=messages[0][\"content\"] if messages else \"\",\n                    timeout=30\n                )\n                return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": result}\n            except Exception as e:\n                return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": str(e)}\n\n        return {\"ok\": False, \"output\": f\"Unknown AI tool: {tool_name}\"}\n\n    # ── Shell Execution ──\n\n    def _exec_shell(self, cmd: str) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Run a shell command with WSL path fixes\"\"\"\n        exec_timeout = self.cfg.get(\"exec_timeout\", 45)\n\n        try:\n            output = subprocess.check_output(\n                cmd, shell=True, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n                timeout=exec_timeout, text=True\n            ).strip()\n            return {\"ok\": True, \"command\": cmd, \"output\": output}\n        except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n            return {\"ok\": False, \"command\": cmd, \"output\": \"⏰ TIMEOUT\"}\n        except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e:\n            msg = (e.output or str(e)).strip()\n            # WSL GPU fix\n            if \"not found\" in msg and cmd == \"nvidia-smi\":\n                try:\n                    output = subprocess.check_output(\n                        \"/mnt/c/Windows/System32/nvidia-smi.exe\",\n                        shell=True, timeout=30, text=True\n                    ).strip()\n                    return {\"ok\": True, \"command\": cmd + \" (→ WSL path)\", \"output\": output}\n                except Exception:\n                    pass\n            return {\"ok\": False, \"command\": cmd, \"output\": msg}\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"ok\": False, \"command\": cmd, \"output\": str(e)}\n\n    # ── Main Execute ──\n\n    def execute(self, plan_text: str, original_request: str,\n                architect_selected_tools: list = None) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"\n        UNIT 3 Main: Extract commands + MCP tools → Execute all → Collect output\n        \"\"\"\n        items = self.extract_commands(plan_text)\n        mcp_selected = architect_selected_tools or []\n\n        # If no items, let local LLM generate commands\n        if not items:\n            items = self._generate_from_plan(plan_text, original_request)\n\n        if not items:\n            return {\n                \"commands_run\": 0, \"outputs\": [],\n                \"success\": False, \"error\": \"Nothing to execute\",\n                \"mcp_tools_used\": []\n            }\n\n        results = []\n        mcp_used = set()\n\n        for item in items:\n            if item[\"type\"] == \"shell\":\n                r = self._exec_shell(item[\"command\"])\n                results.append(r)\n            elif item[\"type\"] == \"mcp\":\n                tool_name = item[\"mcp_tool\"]\n                params = item.get(\"params\", {})\n                mcp_used.add(tool_name)\n\n                if tool_name.startswith(\"filesystem__\"):\n                    r = self._exec_mcp_filesystem(tool_name, params)\n                elif tool_name.startswith(\"web_\"):\n                    r = self._exec_mcp_web(tool_name, params)\n                elif tool_name.startswith(\"ollama__\"):\n                    r = self._exec_mcp_ai(tool_name, params)\n                elif tool_name.startswith(\"terminal__\"):\n                    # Extract command from params\n                    cmd = params.get(\"command\", params.get(\"code\", \"\"))\n                    r = self._exec_shell(cmd) if cmd else {\n                        \"ok\": False, \"command\": tool_name, \"output\": \"No command specified\"}\n                else:\n                    r = {\"ok\": False, \"command\": tool_name,\n                         \"output\": f\"MCP tool not yet implemented: {tool_name}\"}\n\n                r[\"command\"] = f\"[MCP] {tool_name}\"\n                results.append(r)\n\n        # Also mark tools the architect selected\n        for ts in mcp_selected:\n            base_name = ts.split(\" [\")[0] if \" [\" in ts else ts\n            mcp_used.add(base_name)\n\n        all_ok = all(r.get(\"ok\", False) for r in results)\n        return {\n            \"commands_run\": len(results),\n            \"outputs\": results,\n            \"success\": all_ok,\n            \"raw\": \"\\n\".join(\n                f\"$ {r.get('command', '?')}\\n{r.get('output', '')}\" for r in results),\n            \"mcp_tools_used\": sorted(mcp_used),\n        }\n\n    def _generate_from_plan(self, plan_text: str, request: str) -> list[dict]:\n        \"\"\"Local LLM generates commands from plan\"\"\"\n        prompt = f\"\"\"Based on this plan:\n---\n{plan_text[:2000]}\n---\n\nOriginal request: \"{request}\"\n\nGenerate EXACT Linux shell commands (one per line).\nReply with ONLY commands. No markdown.\"\"\"\n\n        try:\n            result = call_llm(\n                self.cfg[\"base_url\"], self.cfg[\"model\"], prompt,\n                api_key=self.cfg.get(\"api_key\", \"ollama\"),\n                system=\"Output shell commands only. No commentary.\",\n                timeout=self.cfg.get(\"timeout\", 60)\n            )\n            items = []\n            for line in result.strip().split(\"\\n\"):\n                line = line.replace(\"`\", \"\").strip()\n                if line and not line.startswith(\"#\"):\n                    items.append({\"type\": \"shell\", \"command\": line})\n            return items\n        except Exception:\n            return []\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# UNIT 4 — REPORTER\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nclass Reporter:\n    \"\"\"UNIT 4: MiniMax สรุปไทยสวยๆ\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, config: dict):\n        self.cfg = config[\"units\"][\"reporter\"]\n        self.local_cfg = config[\"units\"][\"translator\"]\n        self.api_key = KeyVault.find(\n            self.cfg.get(\"api_key_env\", \"OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY\")) or \"\"\n\n    def summarize(self, original_request: str, exec_result: dict,\n                  mcp_tools_used: list = None) -> str:\n        raw_output = exec_result.get(\"raw\", \"\")\n        if not raw_output:\n            return \"ไม่มีผลลัพธ์จากการรันคำสั่ง\"\n\n        if len(raw_output) > 3000:\n            raw_output = raw_output[:3000] + \"\\n…(ตัดทอน)\"\n\n        mcp_line = f\"\\nMCP Tools ที่ใช้: {', '.join(mcp_tools_used)}\" if mcp_tools_used else \"\"\n\n        prompt = f\"\"\"รายงานผลการตรวจสอบระบบ:\n\nคำขอ: {original_request}\n{mcp_line}\n\nผลการทำงาน:\n{raw_output}\n\n---\nสรุปเป็นภาษาไทยสั้น กระชับ (2-4 ประโยค):\"\"\"\n\n        if self.api_key and len(self.api_key) > 10:\n            try:\n                return call_llm(\n                    self.cfg[\"base_url\"], self.cfg[\"model\"], prompt,\n                    api_key=***\n                    system=\"ผู้รายงานผลภาษาไทย เขียนสั้น กระชับ\",\n                    timeout=self.cfg.get(\"timeout\", 120)\n                )\n            except Exception:\n                pass\n\n        try:\n            return call_llm(\n                self.local_cfg[\"base_url\"], self.local_cfg[\"model\"], prompt,\n                api_key=self.local_cfg.get(\"api_key\", \"ollama\"),\n                system=\"สรุปภาษาไทยสั้นๆ\", timeout=90\n            )\n        except Exception:\n            return f\"ผลลัพธ์:\\n{raw_output[:500]}\"\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# CLEANUP\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nclass CleanupManager:\n    \"\"\"Zero Footprint\"\"\"\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def wipe():\n        p = Path(BRIDGE_TMP)\n        if p.exists():\n            shutil.rmtree(p, ignore_errors=True)\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# 4-UNIT + MCP BRIDGE\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nclass FourUnitBridge:\n    \"\"\"\n    ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n    ║  4-UNIT + MCP BRIDGE                           ║\n    ║                                                ║\n    ║  🟢 UNIT 1 — TRANSLATOR   TH→EN               ║\n    ║  🔵 UNIT 2 — ARCHITECT    Plan + MCP Select   ║\n    ║  🟡 UNIT 3 — CODER        Execute + MCP       ║\n    ║  🟣 UNIT 4 — REPORTER     Thai Summary        ║\n    ║  🗑️  CLEANUP               Zero Footprint      ║\n    ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, config_path: str = \"~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/bridge_config.json\"):\n        self.config = load_config(config_path)\n        self.unit1 = Translator(self.config)\n        self.unit2 = Architect(self.config)\n        self.unit3 = Coder(self.config)\n        self.unit4 = Reporter(self.config)\n        self.trace = self.config[\"global\"].get(\"trace\", True)\n        _ensure_tmp()\n\n    def run(self, thai_input: str) -> dict:\n        self._trace(\"═══ 4-UNIT BRIDGE + MCP — START ═══\")\n        self._trace(f\"📥 INPUT: {thai_input[:120]}\")\n\n        # ── UNIT 1: TRANSLATOR ──\n        self._trace(\"\\n🟢 [UNIT 1] TRANSLATOR → TH→EN\")\n        english, ok = self.unit1.translate(thai_input)\n        self._trace(f\"   {'✅' if ok else '⚠️'}  {english[:120]}\")\n\n        # ── MCP DISCOVERY ──\n        self._trace(\"\\n🧰 [MCP DISCOVERY] → Scanning tools…\")\n        mcp_tools = self.unit2.discover_and_prepare()\n        ready = sum(1 for t in mcp_tools.values() if t[\"status\"] == \"ready\")\n        self._trace(f\"   ✅ {ready}/{len(mcp_tools)} MCP tools ready\")\n\n        # ── UNIT 2: ARCHITECT (MCP-aware) ──\n        self._trace(f\"\\n🔵 [UNIT 2] ARCHITECT → {self.unit2.active_model}\")\n        plan = self.unit2.plan(english, mcp_tools)\n        self._trace(f\"   {'✅' if plan['success'] else '❌'}  Plan: {len(plan['raw'])} chars\")\n        self._trace(f\"   🎯 Selected MCP Tools: {', '.join(plan['selected_mcp_tools']) or 'none'}\")\n\n        # ── UNIT 3: CODER ──\n        self._trace(\"\\n🟡 [UNIT 3] CODER → Execute\")\n        exec_result = self.unit3.execute(\n            plan[\"raw\"], thai_input, plan.get(\"selected_mcp_tools\"))\n        ok_count = sum(1 for r in exec_result[\"outputs\"] if r.get(\"ok\"))\n        self._trace(f\"   {'✅' if exec_result['success'] else '⚠️'}  {exec_result['commands_run']} operations ({ok_count} ok)\")\n        for r in exec_result[\"outputs\"]:\n            icon = \"✅\" if r.get(\"ok\") else \"❌\"\n            first_line = r.get(\"output\", \"\").split(\"\\n\")[0][:100]\n            self._trace(f\"      {icon} {r.get('command', '?')[:-50]}\")\n            self._trace(f\"         → {first_line}\")\n\n        # ── UNIT 4: REPORTER ──\n        self._trace(\"\\n🟣 [UNIT 4] REPORTER → Thai Summary\")\n        summary = self.unit4.summarize(\n            thai_input, exec_result, exec_result.get(\"mcp_tools_used\"))\n        self._trace(f\"   ✅ Summary: {summary[:150]}\")\n\n        # ── CLEANUP ──\n        CleanupManager.wipe()\n        self._trace(\"\\n🗑️  CLEANUP → Zero Footprint ✅\")\n        self._trace(\"═══ PIPELINE COMPLETE ═══\\n\")\n\n        return {\n            \"unit1_english\": english,\n            \"unit2_plan\": plan,\n            \"unit3_execution\": exec_result,\n            \"unit4_summary\": summary,\n            \"architect_model\": self.unit2.active_model,\n            \"selected_mcp_tools\": plan.get(\"selected_mcp_tools\", []),\n            \"mcp_tools_used\": exec_result.get(\"mcp_tools_used\", []),\n            \"cleanup_done\": True,\n        }\n\n\n    def _trace(self, msg: str):\n        if self.trace:\n            print(msg, flush=True)\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# CLI\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n        print(\"Usage: python3 universal_bridge.py '<Thai input>'\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    user_input = \" \".join(sys.argv[1:])\n    bridge = FourUnitBridge()\n\n    result = bridge.run(user_input)\n\n    print(\"═\" * 60)\n    print(\"📋  FINAL REPORT\")\n    print(\"═\" * 60)\n    print(f\"🧠 Architect:  {result['architect_model']}\")\n    print(f\"🎯 MCP Tools:  {', '.join(result['selected_mcp_tools']) or 'none'}\")\n    print(f\"🔧 Executed:   {result['unit3_execution']['commands_run']} operations\")\n    print(f\"📝 Thai Summary:\\n   {result['unit4_summary']}\")\n    print(f\"🗑️  Cleanup:    {'✅' if result['cleanup_done'] else '❌'}\")\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama-pay","model":"deepseek-v4-pro:cloud","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778248558460,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1778248577233"}}
