{"type":"compaction","id":"926f1527","parentId":"7e3328ee","timestamp":"2026-05-08T14:06:35.571Z","summary":"## Goal\n1. **Restructure `universal_bridge.py` into 4 \"Army Units\" (เหล่าทัพ)** — strict sequential pipeline:\n   - **UNIT 1: The Translator (Local/Qwen-2.5)** — Thai → short English summary, never send long Thai outward\n   - **UNIT 2: The Architect (Cloud API, swappable)** — Main brain analyze, plan logic steps (NO execution); swappable model (DeepSeek-V3, Claude, etc.) via config\n   - **UNIT 3: The Coder (Local/DeepSeek-Coder)** — Receives plan from Architect → generates code/shell scripts → executes locally → captures output\n   - **UNIT 4: The Reporter (MiniMax-M2.7)** — Takes execution output → summarizes beautiful, readable Thai → reports to user via Telegram\n2. **Easy model-swapping** in UNIT 2 via config file\n3. **Trace logging** at every step showing which Unit is active\n4. **Self-Healing Key Vault** — continuous, never stops from missing keys\n5. **Zero-Footprint** cleanup (all temp in `/tmp/bridge/`, auto-delete)\n6. with: `\"ตรวจสอบการทำงานของ Docker ทุกตัวในเครื่อง \n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user requested a rewrite of `universal_bridge.py` using a new 4-unit architecture.\n\n## Early Progress\n- The assistant analyzed the request and planned a 4-unit architecture:\n  - Unit 1: Translator (Local Qwen-2.5, Thai→EN)\n  - Unit 2: Architect (Cloud API, configurable model, analyze & plan)\n  - Unit 3: Coder (Local code-specialized model, code/execute)\n  - Unit 4: Reporter (MiniMax-M2.7, Thai summary)\n- Core requirements identified: Self-Healing Key, [UNIT X] trace markers, swappable models via config, Zero Footprint.\n- Per AGENTS.md rules, the assistant loaded the mandatory SocratiCode code-analysis skill (SKILL.md) before proceeding with any code editing.\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe conversation was truncated after the assistant read the SocratiCode skill file. The suffix will contain the actual