{"type":"message","id":"bbf05281","parentId":"1fd72744","timestamp":"2026-05-08T14:10:40.465Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The key is `/home/apinan/.opencl...` which is truncated. It looks like the KeyVault found something in a path or config that starts with `/home/apinan/.opencl` — this seems like it found a path string instead of an actual API key! The length is 32 characters, and it starts with `/home/ap` which is clearly a file path, not an API token.\n\nThis means KeyVault is accidentally finding a path value instead of the actual API key. The issue is in one of the layers — probably `openclaw.json` — where a field named `api_key` or similar contains a path like `/home/apinan/.openclaw/...` instead of the actual API token.\n\n\nI need to check what's actually stored in openclaw.json to see which field is being misread as a key.\n","thinkingSignature":"d1bd0693b340d5c6851b9ca7f2967d7f0050a96226d931ad41958f6cb080cfea"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wnlkm4fh70xb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\np = '/home/apinan/.openclaw/openclaw.json'\ndata = json.loads(open(p).read())\n# Find any string > 20 chars that looks like a key/token\ndef find_keys(obj, path=''):\n    if isinstance(obj, str) and len(obj) > 20:\n        if any(k in path.lower() for k in ['key', 'token', 'secret', 'auth']):\n            print(f'{path}: {obj[:50]}...')\n    elif isinstance(obj, dict):\n        for k, v in obj.items():\n            find_keys(v, f'{path}.{k}')\n    elif isinstance(obj, list):\n        for i, v in enumerate(obj):\n            find_keys(v, f'{path}[{i}]')\n\nfind_keys(data)\n\" 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":141,"output":369,"cacheRead":60864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61374,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778249418488,"responseId":"064d2