{"type":"message","id":"6ddff751","parentId":"2d989860","timestamp":"2026-05-08T14:11:16.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The key found starts with `/home/apinan/.opencl...` which is a file PATH, not a token. The KeyVault is returning the wrong thing. It's finding the path to openclaw.json instead of the API key inside it.\n\nLooking at the `_deep_search` function:\n```python\nif isinstance(obj, str) and len(obj) > 15:\n    return obj\n```\n\nThe `_deep_search` checks `isinstance(obj, str) and len(obj) > 15` - any string > 15 chars will be returned. The path `/home/apinan/.openclaw/openclaw.json` is definitely > 15 chars, so it gets returned as if it's a key!\n\n\nThe fix is to increase the minimum length threshold and add a check that specifically excludes file paths, since the token string itself should be much shorter than a typical path.\n","thinkingSignature":"64ca15d42bfb5f02fb4accde43ea5d8c73e19c0621cc1d1c8a8d37bb430c89bd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l71ggd285dbj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json, os\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ndef fix_key_vault():\n    oc_path = Path('~/.openclaw/openclaw.json').expanduser()\n    if oc_path.exists():\n        data = json.loads(oc_path.read_text())\n        # Get minimax key directly\n        try:\n            key = data['models']['providers']['minimax']['apiKey']\n            os.environ['OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY'] = key\n            print(f'Set OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY = {key[:25]}...')\n        except:\n            pass\n\nfix_key_vault()\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":285,"output":322,"cacheRead":61440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62047,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778249464859,"responseId":"064d21fa557c9b5f4ab7f81f0bd4b8a8"}}
