{"type":"message","id":"8ae0c346","parentId":"0562e17d","timestamp":"2026-05-08T14:12:21.803Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Architect is returning only 104 chars and the plan is failing. The issue is that MiniMax's response contains \"Invalid token\" - it seems like MiniMax is returning an error message rather than a plan. This might mean the API is rejecting the request.\n\nWait - I see the issue now. The Architect's `plan()` function gets a 401 error from MiniMax, so it returns `{\"raw\": \"[HTTP ERROR 401]: ...\", \"success\": False, ...}`. But the trace shows \"Plan: 104 chars\" which means the raw response is the error message (104 chars). That's why it says \"❌ Plan: 104 chars\".\n \nThe API key I'm setting in the config might not be getting passed correctly to the call_llm function, or maybe MiniMax needs the key in a different header format. Let me verify the key is actually being used when making the request.\n","thinkingSignature":"b29dee66eaf8ba4f29785957c04fd884f6d4a10e43047bfee91e0e6104e492fb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lps6170hw9ml_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport urllib.request, json\n\nkey = 'sk-cp-kjq0vJ8QYii1G-PWikNeEF6oMx_ySJqpb-icTKILATzP'\nbody = json.dumps({\n    'model': 'minimax/MiniMax-M2.7',\n    'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'Say hello in 3 words'}],\n    'temperature': 0.3\n}).encode()\n\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\n    'https://ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com/api/v1/chat/completions',\n    data=body,\n    headers={'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Authorization': f'Bearer {key}'}\n)\nwith urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=30) as resp:\n    data = json.loads(resp.read())\n    print(data['choices'][0]['message']['content'])\n\"","timeout":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":753,"output":409,"cacheRead":62848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64010,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead