{"type":"message","id":"d5488ef4","parentId":"d2473ea3","timestamp":"2026-05-08T14:13:01.906Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both keys fail. The issue is that `ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com` is an OpenAI-compatible proxy, and it might need a specific internal format. Let me check what OpenClaw uses - maybe the key needs to be passed differently, or the URL is different.\n\nActually, from MEMORY.md I see:\n- primary model: thaigq/deepseek-v4-pro:cloud\n- fallbacks: thaigq/deepseek-v4-flash:cloud, thaigq/minimax-m2.7:cloud\n- Provider: thaigq (https://ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com/api/v1)\n\n\nBut the config uses `minimax/MiniMax-M2.7` with the `***...` key. The real problem might be that `ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com` requires a different authentication format than standard Bearer tokens - OpenClaw itself uses these keys successfully, so there may be a gateway or routing layer involved that I'm not accounting for.\n\nThe most likely culprit is that the key has been rotated or is no longer valid in config but is still being used somewhere.\n","thinkingSignature":"ac7675d87464b51535791e0cd4975282bddb908b2adfe5ac591dd4975cc85ea9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c8z57iynsdxm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config get models.providers 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor k, v in data.items():\n    if isinstance(v, dict):\n        print(k, '-> apiKey:', v.get('apiKey', 'N/A')[:30] if v.get('apiKey') else 'N/A')\n\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":246,"output":354,"cacheRead":64256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64856,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778249556991,"responseId":"064d2256bcef3300dfeea9fe9f1f18d8"}}
