{"type":"message","id":"886b3b65","parentId":"09ab7a11","timestamp":"2026-05-08T14:14:03.309Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The key is 125 characters long - that's clearly not a simple API key. Looking at the key structure, it looks like a JWT token or some other complex format. Let me check if there's a different API endpoint format needed for this service.\n\nActually, let me look at how OpenClaw itself makes requests. OpenClaw uses the same endpoint `https://ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com/api/v1` and works fine. So the endpoint is correct. The issue is that the key format or the way we're using it is wrong.\n\nLet me think about this differently - the key might need to be sent in a different header format, or the model name format might be different. Let me check the OpenClaw source code for how it makes requests to this endpoint.\n\nActually wait - looking at the earlier API response, it said `Token ที่ใช้ไม่ถูกต้อง` which means \"the token used is incorrect\". But OpenClaw uses the same key and works. So maybe the issue is that the key we read from openclaw.json is the wrong one - maybe OpenClaw has its own internal key management.\n\nLet me just set the key from the config file directly into the bridge_config.json and see if that helps. The key I extracted was 125 chars which seems like a JWT. But when I tested the shorter key first, it also failed.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach - just use the deepseek key directly in the config and see if it works:\n","thinkingSignature":"2bd940b29b932024e23b55b5f7427159cf9b20700e0dcfa1ea18902501feaa00"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k0poslwkojug_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport urllib.request, json\n\n# Try deepseek key\nwith open('/home/apinan/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    data = json.load(f)\n\nkey = data['models']['providers']['deepseek']['apiKey']\nprint(f\"DeepSeek key length: {len(key)}\")\n\nbody = json.dumps({\n    'model': 'deepseek-chat',\n    'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'Say hello in 3 words'}],\n    'temperature': 0.3\n}).encode()\n\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\n    'https://ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com/api/v1/chat/completions',\n    data=body,\n    headers={'Authorization': f'Bearer {key}', 'Content-Type': 'application/json'}\n)\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=30) as resp:\n        result = json.loads(resp.read())\n        print('✅ DeepSeek works:', result['choices'][0]['message']['content'])\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print('❌ DeepSeek failed:', e)\nPYEOF","timeout":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":309,"output":580,"cacheRead":66560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67449,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778249623208,"responseId":"064d2298a2dbd0bcaadd036512cb7c56"}}
