{"type":"message","id":"3af2d97c","parentId":"2b4a78bc","timestamp":"2026-05-08T14:15:22.085Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear now. The Architect is receiving a 401 from the cloud, but the local terminal commands run. The problem is that the Architect plan only has 104 chars - that's way too short for a real plan. Something is wrong with the call_llm to the cloud endpoint.\n\nActually wait - looking at the trace more carefully:\n- The Architect plan is 104 chars (too short, real plan would be much longer)\n- The output shows \"Invalid token\" \n\nThis suggests the call_llm to the cloud API is failing with 401 and returning a truncated response.\n\nBut I just tested with curl and it worked with `sk-e53…5ac4`. So why is Python failing?\n\n\nLet me trace through the API call in Python to see what's actually being sent.\n","thinkingSignature":"a0c8ce5516a3950cf8b32ea2de6033f4c0fd899e688c9d679425a3648f2a4e95"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7s3qf9irgaxi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport urllib.request, json, sys\n\n# Test the exact same call that bridge uses\nbase_url = \"https://ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com/api/v1\"\nmodel = \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\"\napi_key = \"sk-e53c34aec86b4a5188a9d44ce6455ac4\"\n\nbody = json.dumps({\n    \"model\": model,\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful assistant.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Say hello in 3 words\"}],\n    \"temperature\": 0.3,\n}).encode()\n\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\n    f\"{base_url}/chat/completions\",\n    data=body,\n    headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {api_key}\"}\n)\n\nprint(f\"URL: {req.full_url}\")\nprint(f\"Headers: {req.headers}\")\nprint(f\"Body: {body.decode()[:100]}\")\n\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=30) as resp:\n        raw = json.loads(resp.read())\n        print(\"✅ Response:\", raw[\"choices\"][0][\"message\"][\"content\"])\nexcept urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n    body_err = e.read().decode(errors=\"replace\")\n    print(f\"❌ HTTP {e.code}: {body_err[:200]}\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"❌ Error: {e}\")\nPYEOF","timeout":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":863,"output":527,"cacheRead":67776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69166,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778249705022,"responseId":"064d22ea22d05032e61d4a0a2fe3278a"}}
