{"type":"message","id":"b6b91f44","parentId":"1c814e32","timestamp":"2026-05-08T14:15:55.584Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Direct call works fine! The issue is the bridge code is NOT using `api_key` from config. Let me check why the bridge is still getting 401. I think the problem is the `call_llm` function is NOT using `api_key=self.api_key` - it's using `api_key=` parameter but the Architect's `self.api_key` is set via `KeyVault.find()` which finds something wrong.\n\nLet me trace the flow:\n1. Architect.__init__ calls `KeyVault.find(self.cfg.get(\"api_key_env\", \"OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY\"))` which sets `self.api_key`\n2. But if config has `api_key` directly, the function still uses `KeyVault.find()` which might find something else\n\n\n3. I need to add debug output to the bridge to see what `self.api_key` actually contains in the Architect class\n","thinkingSignature":"9cf36c614f2819aa6367680f1b61f5911d3ab9a4470ce5d8c042e2afd79f9043"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2fzw72fcqmub_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts')\n\n# Patch Architect to debug\nimport universal_bridge as ub\n\noriginal_init = ub.Architect.__init__\ndef debug_init(self, config):\n    original_init(self, config)\n    print(f\"DEBUG: architect api_key = {self.api_key[:20] if self.api_key else 'EMPTY'}...\")\n    print(f\"DEBUG: config api_key = {config['units']['architect'].get('api_key', 'NOT SET')[:20]}...\")\n\nub.Architect.__init__ = debug_init\n\nbridge = ub.FourUnitBridge()\nPYEOF","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":215,"output":352,"cacheRead":68992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69559,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778249740828,"responseId":"064d230eb60cbf361fb2cd26c6cd212d"}}
