{"type":"message","id":"5132d383","parentId":"1cc0c96c","timestamp":"2026-05-08T14:16:16.475Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the bug! The `KeyVault.find()` is returning the wrong value first (from ~/.hermes/.env which starts with `/home/apinan/.opencl...`). The config-level `api_key` (which is correct) is being ignored because KeyVault takes priority in `__init__`.\n\nI need to fix the Architect's `__init__` to prefer the config-level `api_key` over KeyVault when both exist, OR fix the KeyVault priority to not check hermes .env first.\n\nLet me fix the Architect class to handle this properly.\n","thinkingSignature":"d45ca46285ed6762e9b2a59ded55c7d7178a3ed0aeba196343744e169998a081"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nFound it! `KeyVault` ดึงคีย์ผิดจาก `~/.hermes/.env` ก่อน config ที่ถูกต้อง แก้ตรงนี้เลย:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uolw2hqhmdfx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\n# Read the file\nwith open('/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Fix Architect.__init__ to prefer config api_key over KeyVault\n# Old pattern:\n#   self.api_key = KeyVault.find(...) or \"\"\n# Should check config api_key FIRST, then KeyVault\n\nold_architect_init = '''    def __init__(self, config: dict):\n        self.cfg = config[\"units\"][\"architect\"]\n        self.global_cfg = config[\"global\"]\n        self.api_key = KeyVault.find(\n            self.cfg.get(\"api_key_env\", \"OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY\")) or \"\"'''\n\nnew_architect_init = '''    def __init__(self, config: dict):\n        self.cfg = config[\"units\"][\"architect\"]\n        self.global_cfg = config[\"global\"]\n        # Prefer config-level api_key over KeyVault\n        self.api_key = self.cfg.get(\"api_key\") or KeyVault.find(\n            self.cfg.get(\"api_key_env\", \"OLLAMA_PAY_API_KEY\")) or \"\"'''\n\nif old_architect_init in content:\n    content = content.replace(old_architect_init, new_architect_init)\n    print(\"Fixed Architect.__init__\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Pattern not found, showing around line 459:\")\n    lines = content.split('\\n')\n    for i, line in enumerate(lines[455:475], 456):\n        print(f\"{i}: {line}\")\n\nwith open('/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py', 'w') as f:\n    f.write(content)\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":242,"output":539,"cacheRead":69184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69965,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778249755672,"responseId":"064d231d0d94aedefb86749b22f67bf2"}}
