{"type":"message","id":"978ed14c","parentId":"79ba38d5","timestamp":"2026-05-08T14:20:42.167Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to adjust the path so it correctly points to the workspace. Let me fix the bridge to use the correct workspace path. The workspace is at `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/`.\n\nLet me update the bridge to:\n1. Use the correct workspace path\n2. The user's work folder appears to be `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/` or Windows path `C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Desktop\\Work Auto`\n\nActually, looking at the ls output, the workspace is `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/`. But the user mentioned \"โฟลเดอร์งาน\" (work folder). Let me check what folders exist that could be the \"work folder.\"\n\n\nI see Windows-style paths in the workspace like `D:\\ComfyUI_windows_portable\\...` which suggests the work folder is likely `C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Desktop\\Work Auto\\` or similar locations. I'll update the bridge to scan the workspace directory using the native Python filesystem tools instead of relying on shell commands, and fix the `filesystem__search_files` to use the correct path.","thinkingSignature":"fad3e7ed670a96373d0e743a6330da91149823a1386afea8c3a383f83ebcca53"},{"type":"text","text":"รับเลย! กำลังแก้ path ให้ตรง + ปรับ filesystem MCP ให้รู้จัก workspace จริง:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wagen2dbxj8n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nwith open('/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# 1. Add workspace path constant\nold_tmp = 'BRIDGE_TMP = \"/tmp/bridge\"'\nnew_tmp = '''BRIDGE_TMP = \"/tmp/bridge\"\nWORKSPACE_PATHS = [\n    \"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace\",\n    \"/home/apinan/.openclaw\",\n    \"/home/apinan\",\n]'''\n\ncontent = content.replace(old_tmp, new_tmp)\n\n# 2. Update _exec_mcp_filesystem to try workspace paths for relative paths\nold_exec = '''    def _exec_mcp_filesystem(self, tool_name: str, params: dict) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Execute filesystem MCP tools natively in Python\"\"\"\n        path = params.get(\"path\", \".\")'''\n\nnew_exec = '''    def _exec_mcp_filesystem(self, tool_name: str, params: dict) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Execute filesystem MCP tools natively in Python\"\"\"\n        path = params.get(\"path\", \".\")\n\n        # Resolve path - try as-is first, then check workspace paths\n        def resolve_path(p):\n            if not p or p == \".\":\n                return \"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace\"\n            p = os.path.expanduser(p)\n            if os.path.exists(p):\n                return p\n            # Try prepending workspace\n            for wp in WORKSPACE_PATHS:\n                candidate = os.path.join(wp, os.path.basename(p))\n                if os.path.exists(candidate):\n                    return candidate\n            return p\n\n        path = resolve_path(path)'''\n\ncontent = content.replace(old_exec, new_exec)\n\n# 3. Also update shell command execution to use workspace path\nold_coder_shell = '''    def _exec_shell(self, cmd: str) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Run a shell command with WSL path fixes\"\"\"\n        exec_timeout = self.cfg.get(\"exec_timeout\", 45)\n\n        try:\n            output = subprocess.check_output(\n                cmd, shell=True, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n                timeout=exec_timeout, text=True\n            ).strip()\n            return {\"ok\": True, \"command\": cmd, \"output\": output}\n        except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n            return {\"ok\": False, \"command\": cmd, \"output\": \"⏰ TIMEOUT\"}\n        except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e:\n            msg = (e.output or str(e)).strip()\n            # WSL GPU fix\n            if \"not found\" in msg and cmd == \"nvidia-smi\":\n                try:\n                    output = subprocess.check_output(\n                        \"/mnt/c/Windows/System32/nvidia-smi.exe\",\n                        shell=True, timeout=30, text=True\n                    ).strip()\n                    return {\"ok\": True, \"command\": cmd + \" (→ WSL path)\", \"output\": output}\n                except Exception:\n                    pass\n            return {\"ok\": False, \"command\": cmd, \"output\": msg}\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"ok\": False, \"command\": cmd, \"output\": str(e)}'''\n\nnew_coder_shell = '''    def _exec_shell(self, cmd: str) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Run a shell command with WSL path fixes\"\"\"\n        exec_timeout = self.cfg.get(\"exec_timeout\", 45)\n\n        # Expand ~ in commands to workspace\n        cmd = os.path.expanduser(cmd)\n\n        try:\n            output = subprocess.check_output(\n                cmd, shell=True, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n                timeout=exec_timeout, text=True\n            ).strip()\n            return {\"ok\": True, \"command\": cmd, \"output\": output}\n        except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n            return {\"ok\": False, \"command\": cmd, \"output\": \"⏰ TIMEOUT\"}\n        except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e:\n            msg = (e.output or str(e)).strip()\n            # WSL GPU fix\n            if \"not found\" in msg and cmd == \"nvidia-smi\":\n                try:\n                    output = subprocess.check_output(\n                        \"/mnt/c/Windows/System32/nvidia-smi.exe\",\n                        shell=True, timeout=30, text=True\n                    ).strip()\n                    return {\"ok\": True, \"command\": cmd + \" (→ WSL path)\", \"output\": output}\n                except Exception:\n                    pass\n            return {\"ok\": False, \"command\": cmd, \"output\": msg}\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"ok\": False, \"command\": cmd, \"output\": str(e)}'''\n\ncontent = content.replace(old_coder_shell, new_coder_shell)\n\nwith open('/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/universal_bridge.py', 'w') as f:\n    f.write(content)\nprint(\"✅ Updated path resolution + workspace detection\")\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":203,"output":1330,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":73697,"totalTokens":75230,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778250014033,"responseId":"064d2420c2ca17c2d8cf64bda7225409"}}
