{"type":"message","id":"7388dd0d","parentId":"75cc386a","timestamp":"2026-05-08T16:12:20.013Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether OpenClaw stores/saves conversation context (tokens) like this - meaning, does OpenClaw keep piling up context across messages. They want to know if OpenClaw has a mechanism for this.\n\nLet me think about what OpenClaw does with context:\n\n1. Each session has a context window that includes previous messages\n2. The system injects files like MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, AGENTS.md etc. into every conversation\n3. There's a cache boundary in MEMORY.md that separates static from dynamic content\n4. The \"compact\" mechanism exists (the summary at the start of this conversation shows compaction happened before)\n5. There's no built-in auto-cleanup of old messages in a session\n\nLet me check the OpenClaw docs to see how context management works.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_y6tysx5k","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"OpenClaw session context management token limit compaction"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama-pay","model":"deepseek-v4-pro:cloud","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778256720034,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1778256736722"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5ab465f3","parentId":"7388dd0d","timestamp":"2026-05-08T16:12:21.761Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_y6tysx5k","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"OpenClaw session context management token limit compaction\",\n  \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1153,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0af877e3e205f964\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSession management deep dive - OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0af877e3e205f964\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/reference/session-management-compaction\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"48fc4a375a17ea97\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nContext limits ( context window vs tracked tokens ) Compaction (manual and auto- compaction ) and where to hook pre- compaction work Silent housekeeping (memory writes that should not produce user-visible output) If you want a higher-level overview first, start with: Session management Compaction Memory overview Memory search Session pruning ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"48fc4a375a17ea97\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"docs.openclaw.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"289df1c995636e5d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSessions & Context Management | openclaw/docs | DeepWiki\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"289df1c995636e5d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://deepwiki.com/openclaw/docs/8-sessions-and-context-management\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e0ea9753d6d611cd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCompaction (If Needed): If the context exceeds token limits , the compaction pipeline triggers to summarize or prune history. For details on how sessions are stored and formatted, see Session Management & Compaction . The Compaction Pipeline To prevent \\\" context overflow\\\" errors, OpenClaw employs a compaction engine.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e0ea9753d6d611cd\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"deepwiki.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b9421fcbb5ed2d17\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCompaction | OpenClaw Docs\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b9421fcbb5ed2d17\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://openclaw-ai.com/en/docs/concepts/compaction\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cc75652a003c3548\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nContext Window & Compaction Every model has a context window (max tokens it can see). Long-running chats accumulate messages and tool results; once the window is tight, OpenClaw compacts older history to stay within limits . What compaction is Compaction summarizes older conversation into a compact summary entry and keeps recent messages intact. The summary is stored in the session history, so ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cc75652a003c3548\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"openclaw-ai.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e409457b2e0b0ebf\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nsession-management-compaction.md - GitHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e409457b2e0b0ebf\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/extradimen/openclaw-multiuser-platform/blob/main/openclaw-20260505/docs/reference/session-management-compaction.md\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ff22ab5e8a3cea49\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSession routing (how inbound messages map to a sessionKey) Session store ( sessions .json) and what it tracks Transcript persistence (*.jsonl) and its structure Transcript hygiene (provider-specific fixups before runs) Context limits ( context window vs tracked tokens ) Compaction (manual and auto- compaction ) and where to hook pre- compaction work Silent housekeeping (memory writes that should not ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ff22ab5e8a3cea49\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7efdd1f7a06d3ed6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSession Management Deep Dive - OpenClaw - Open Source AI Coding Assistant\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7efdd1f7a06d3ed6\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://openclawlab.com/en/docs/reference/session-management-compaction/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6382de60ee9c2a2b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThis document explains how OpenClaw manages sessions end-to-end: Session routing (how inbound messages map to a sessionKey) Session store ( sessions .json) and what it tracks Transcript persistence (*.jsonl) and its structure Transcript hygiene (provider-specific fixups before runs) Context limits ( context window vs tracked tokens ) Compaction (manual + auto- compaction ) and where to hook pre ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6382de60ee9c2a2b\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"openclawlab.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"OpenClaw session context management token limit compaction","provider":"duckduckgo","count":5,"tookMs":1153,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"duckduckgo","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0af877e3e205f964\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSession management deep dive - OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0af877e3e205f964\">>>","url":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/reference/session-management-compaction","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"48fc4a375a17ea97\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nContext limits ( context window vs tracked tokens ) Compaction (manual and auto- compaction ) and where to hook pre- compaction work Silent housekeeping (memory writes that should not produce user-visible output) If you want a higher-level overview first, start with: Session management Compaction Memory overview Memory search Session pruning ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"48fc4a375a17ea97\">>>","siteName":"docs.openclaw.ai"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"289df1c995636e5d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSessions & Context Management | openclaw/docs | DeepWiki\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"289df1c995636e5d\">>>","url":"https://deepwiki.com/openclaw/docs/8-sessions-and-context-management","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e0ea9753d6d611cd\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nCompaction (If Needed): If the context exceeds token limits , the compaction pipeline triggers to summarize or prune history. For details on how sessions are stored and formatted, see Session Management & Compaction . The Compaction Pipeline To prevent \" context overflow\" errors, OpenClaw employs a compaction engine.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e0ea9753d6d611cd\">>>","siteName":"deepwiki.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b9421fcbb5ed2d17\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nCompaction | OpenClaw Docs\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b9421fcbb5ed2d17\">>>","url":"https://openclaw-ai.com/en/docs/concepts/compaction","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cc75652a003c3548\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nContext Window & Compaction Every model has a context window (max tokens it can see). Long-running chats accumulate messages and tool results; once the window is tight, OpenClaw compacts older history to stay within limits . What compaction is Compaction summarizes older conversation into a compact summary entry and keeps recent messages intact. The summary is stored in the session history, so ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cc75652a003c3548\">>>","siteName":"openclaw-ai.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=